INSERT INTO `tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd` (`uid`, `pid`, `tstamp`, `crdate`, `deleted`, `hidden`, `starttime`, `endtime`, `sorting`, `sys_language_uid`, `l10n_parent`, `l10n_state`, `l10n_diffsource`, `t3ver_oid`, `t3ver_wsid`, `t3ver_state`, `t3ver_stage`, `title`, `description`, `version`, `slug`, `categories`, `syllabusdescription`, `link`, `edited`, `images`, `makenewtranslation`, `related_tccds`, `links`) VALUES
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (1, 11, 1707659356, 1706618385, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2816, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'XLIFF / locallang.xlf [1]', '<h2>Create</h2>\r\n<h3>Complete file: Resources/Private/Language/locallang.xlf</h3>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\" standalone=\"yes\" ?&gt;\r\n&lt;xliff version=\"1.0\"&gt;\r\n    &lt;file source-language=\"en\" datatype=\"plaintext\" original=\"EXT:tccd_examples/Resources/Private/Language/locallang_db.xlf\" date=\"2024-01-30T13:30:45Z\" product-name=\"tccd_examples\"&gt;\r\n       &lt;header/&gt;\r\n       &lt;body&gt;\r\n          &lt;trans-unit id=\"pi_flexform.sheetGeneral\" resname=\"pi_flexform.sheetGeneral\"&gt;\r\n             &lt;source&gt;Tccd Plugin&lt;/source&gt;\r\n          &lt;/trans-unit&gt;\r\n          &lt;trans-unit id=\"singlePid\" resname=\"singlePid\"&gt;\r\n             &lt;source&gt;Single Page ID&lt;/source&gt;\r\n          &lt;/trans-unit&gt;\r\n&nbsp;          ...\r\n       &lt;/body&gt;\r\n    &lt;/file&gt;\r\n&lt;/xliff&gt;</pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Read</h2>\r\n<h3>In Configuration/Flexforms/TccdPlugin.xml</h3>\r\n<pre>\r\nLLL:EXT:tccd_examples/Resources/Private/Language/locallang_db.xlf:singlePid</pre>', 1, 'xliff-locallangxlf', 1, '<p>Working with XLIFF files in TYPO3 for multilingual websites. Includes writing and extending XLIFF files, overriding translations in TypoScript, and using the f:translate ViewHelper.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Goals</strong></h3>\r\n<ul> 	<li>I know what XLIFF is.</li> 	<li>I know how to write and extend an XLIFF file.</li> 	<li>I know how to introduce new languages and generate the needed XLIFF file.</li> 	<li>I know how to override the translations of an extension in TypoScript.</li> 	<li>I know how to access the translations with the f:translate-Viewhelper</li> </ul>', '', 0, '1', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (2, 11, 1706789894, 1706619049, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2560, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Flexform Concepts [2]', '<h2>Create</h2>\r\n<h3>1. Complete file: Configuration/Flexforms/TccdPlugin.xml</h3>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;T3DataStructure&gt;\r\n    &lt;meta&gt;\r\n        &lt;langDisable&gt;1&lt;/langDisable&gt;\r\n    &lt;/meta&gt;\r\n    &lt;sheets&gt;\r\n        &lt;sDEF&gt;\r\n            &lt;ROOT&gt;\r\n                &lt;sheetTitle&gt;\r\n                    LLL:EXT:tccd_examples/Resources/Private/Language/locallang_db.xlf:pi_flexform.sheetGeneral\r\n                &lt;/sheetTitle&gt;\r\n                &lt;type&gt;array&lt;/type&gt;\r\n                &lt;el&gt;\r\n                    &lt;settings.singlePid&gt;\r\n                        &lt;label&gt;\r\n                            LLL:EXT:tccd_examples/Resources/Private/Language/locallang_db.xlf:singlePid\r\n                        &lt;/label&gt;\r\n                        &lt;config&gt;\r\n                            &lt;type&gt;group&lt;/type&gt;\r\n                            &lt;allowed&gt;pages&lt;/allowed&gt;\r\n                            &lt;maxitems&gt;1&lt;/maxitems&gt;\r\n                            &lt;minitems&gt;0&lt;/minitems&gt;\r\n                            &lt;size&gt;1&lt;/size&gt;\r\n                            &lt;suggestOptions&gt;\r\n                                &lt;default&gt;\r\n                                    &lt;additionalSearchFields&gt;nav_title, alias, url&lt;/additionalSearchFields&gt;\r\n                                    &lt;addWhere&gt;AND pages.doktype = 1&lt;/addWhere&gt;\r\n                                &lt;/default&gt;\r\n                            &lt;/suggestOptions&gt;\r\n                        &lt;/config&gt;\r\n                    &lt;/settings.singlePid&gt;\r\n                &lt;/el&gt;\r\n            &lt;/ROOT&gt;\r\n        &lt;/sDEF&gt;\r\n    &lt;/sheets&gt;\r\n&lt;/T3DataStructure&gt;\r\n</pre>\r\n<h3>2. Configuration/TCA/Overrides/tt_content.php</h3>\r\n<pre>\r\n$GLOBALS[\'TCA\'][\'tt_content\'][\'types\'][\'list\'][\'subtypes_excludelist\'][\'tccdexamples_tccdpluginlist\'] = \'layout,select_key\';\r\n$GLOBALS[\'TCA\'][\'tt_content\'][\'types\'][\'list\'][\'subtypes_addlist\'][\'tccdexamples_tccdpluginlist\'] = \'pi_flexform\';\r\n\r\n\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Utility\\ExtensionManagementUtility::addPiFlexFormValue(\r\n    \'tccdexamples_tccdpluginlist\',\r\n    \'FILE:EXT:tccd_examples/Configuration/Flexforms/TccdPlugin.xml\'\r\n);</pre>\r\n<h2>Read</h2>\r\n<p>In file:&nbsp;Resources/Private/Templates/Tccd/List.html</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n{settings.singlePid}\r\n</pre>\r\n<h2>Where are flexform data stored?</h2>\r\n<p>They are stored in the database in the field pi_flexform of the plugin of the tt_content table.</p>\r\n<ul> </ul>', 1, 'flexform-concepts', 2, '<p>Basics about the concept of Flexforms and how it relates to the TCA.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Goals</strong></h3>\r\n<ul> 	<li>I know what a Flexform data structure is and how it compares to a similar TCA data structure.</li> 	<li>I know how data for a Flexform field is stored.</li> 	<li>I can implement a Flexform data structure in XML.</li> 	<li>I can configure a Flexform field to use my XML data structure.</li> </ul>', '', 0, '1', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (3, 11, 1706792241, 1706619303, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2176, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Doctrine DBAL [3]', '<h2>Usecase: Search by searchterm</h2>\r\n<h3>In file Classes/Domain/Repository/TccdRepository.php</h3>\r\n<pre>\r\n/**\r\n * action findBySearchterm\r\n *\r\n * @param string $searchTerm\r\n * @return object\r\n */\r\npublic function findBySearchterm($searchTerm) {\r\n\r\n    // Doctrine DBAL [3]\r\n    $query = $this-&gt;createQuery();\r\n    $query-&gt;matching($query-&gt;like(\'title\', \"%\".$searchTerm.\"%\")); // Queries in the&nbsp;query&nbsp;language of Extbase are automatically escaped\r\n    $query-&gt;setOrderings(array(\'title\' =&gt; \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Extbase\\Persistence\\Generic\\Query::ORDER_ASCENDING));\r\n    return $query-&gt;execute();\r\n}</pre>\r\n<h2>Description</h2>\r\n<p>In TYPO3, database queries can be implemented in the MVC model via the repository or manually via the query builder. The query builder is useful if you want to create database queries for tables that do not have a model or if more complex database queries are necessary. INNER and LEFT JOINS can also be implemented using the query builder.</p>\r\n<h2>Hints</h2>\r\n<ul> 	<li>Queries in the&nbsp;query&nbsp;language of Extbase are automatically escaped. In TYPO3 Repositories $this is of type TYPO3\\CMS\\Extbase\\Persistence\\QueryInterface.</li> 	<li>If you use QueryBuilder: Never instantiate and initialize the query builder manually using dependency injection or&nbsp;GeneralUtility::makeInstance(), otherwise you will miss essential dependencies and runtime setup.</li> 	<li>The QueryBuilder holds internal state and must not be reused for different queries. In addition, a reuse comes with a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.derhansen.de/2023/10/the-pitfalls-of-reusing-typo3-querybuilder-analyzing-a-performance-bottleneck.html\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">significant performance penalty and memory consumption</a>.&nbsp;<strong>Use one query builder per query.</strong>&nbsp;Get a fresh one by calling&nbsp;$connection-&gt;createQueryBuilder()&nbsp;if the same table is involved, or use&nbsp;$connectionPool-&gt;getQueryBuilderForTable()&nbsp;for a query to a different table. Do not worry, creating those object instances is quite fast.</li> </ul>\r\n<h2>Links</h2>\r\n<ul> 	<li><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/QueryBuilder/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/QueryBuilder/Index.htm</a></li> 	<li><a href=\"https://t3campus.de/typo3-lernen/der-typo3-querybuilder/\">https://t3campus.de/typo3-lernen/der-typo3-querybuilder/</a>&nbsp;(DE)</li> </ul>', 1, 'doctrine-dbal', 2, '<p>Basic knowledge about the Doctrine component for transparently accessing several DBMS in PHP.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>TCCD Goals</strong></h3>\r\n<ul> 	<li>I know what Doctrine DBAL is.</li> 	<li>I know the difference between Doctrine DBAL and Doctrine ORM.</li> 	<li>I know the role of Doctrine DBAL in TYPO3.</li> </ul>', '', 1, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (4, 11, 1706740800, 1706704059, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2112, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'File abstraction layer (FAL) [4]', '<p><strong>The file abstraction layer (FAL) is a toolbox for dealing with media.&nbsp;</strong><br /> &nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>1. TCA in file Configuration/TCA/tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd.php</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\n// [4] - File abstraction layer (FAL)\r\n\'images\' =&gt; [\r\n    \'exclude\' =&gt; true,\r\n    \'label\' =&gt; \'LLL:EXT:tccd_examples/Resources/Private/Language/locallang_db.xlf:tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd.images\',\r\n    \'config\' =&gt; \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Utility\\ExtensionManagementUtility::getFileFieldTCAConfig(\r\n        \'images\',\r\n        [\r\n            \'appearance\' =&gt; [\r\n                \'createNewRelationLinkTitle\' =&gt; \'LLL:EXT:frontend/Resources/Private/Language/locallang_ttc.xlf:images.addFileReference\'\r\n            ],\r\n            \'foreign_types\' =&gt; [\r\n                \'0\' =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ],\r\n                \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\File::FILETYPE_TEXT =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ],\r\n                \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\File::FILETYPE_IMAGE =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ],\r\n                \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\File::FILETYPE_AUDIO =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ],\r\n                \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\File::FILETYPE_VIDEO =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ],\r\n                \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\File::FILETYPE_APPLICATION =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ]\r\n            ],\r\n            \'foreign_match_fields\' =&gt; [\r\n                \'fieldname\' =&gt; \'images\',\r\n                \'tablenames\' =&gt; \'tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd\',\r\n                \'table_local\' =&gt; \'sys_file\',\r\n            ],\r\n            \'maxitems\' =&gt; 1\r\n        ],\r\n        $GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'GFX\'][\'imagefile_ext\']\r\n    ),\r\n],</pre>\r\n<p>...</p>\r\n<h2>2. Model adaption in file Classes/Domain/Model/Tccd.php</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\n/**\r\n * @var ObjectStorage&lt;FileReference&gt;\r\n * @Lazy\r\n */\r\nprotected ObjectStorage $images;\r\n\r\npublic function initializeObject(): void\r\n{\r\n    $this-&gt;category = new ObjectStorage();\r\n    $this-&gt;images = new ObjectStorage();\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>...</p>\r\n<pre>\r\npublic function addImages(FileReference $images): void\r\n{\r\n    $this-&gt;images-&gt;attach($images);\r\n}\r\n\r\npublic function removeImages(FileReference $imagesToRemove): void\r\n{\r\n    $this-&gt;images-&gt;detach($imagesToRemove);\r\n}\r\n\r\npublic function getImages(): ?ObjectStorage\r\n{\r\n    return $this-&gt;images;\r\n}\r\n\r\npublic function setImages(?ObjectStorage $images): void\r\n{\r\n    $this-&gt;images = $images;\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<ul> </ul>\r\n<h2>3. Output in file Resources/Private/Partials/Tccd/Properties.html</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;f:comment&gt;[4] - File abstraction layer (FAL)&lt;/f:comment&gt;\r\n&lt;f:if condition=\"{tccd.images}\"&gt;\r\n    &lt;div class=\"tccd-images\"&gt;\r\n       &lt;f:for each=\"{tccd.images}\" as=\"image\"&gt;\r\n          &lt;div class=\"tccd-image-item\"&gt;\r\n             &lt;f:image src=\"{image.uid}\" alt=\"\" treatIdAsReference=\"TRUE\" width=\"{settings.detail.imageWidth}\" height=\"{settings.detail.imageHeight}\" /&gt;\r\n          &lt;/div&gt;\r\n       &lt;/f:for&gt;\r\n    &lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;/f:if&gt;\r\n\r\n</pre>\r\n<h2>Links</h2>\r\n<ul> 	<li><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/Fal/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/Fal/Index.html</a></li> </ul>', 1, 'file-abstraction-layer-fal-4', 1, '<p>Know about transparent inclusion of external file sources into TYPO3.</p>\r\n<h3>Goals</h3>\r\n<ul> 	<li>I know there is an abstraction layer between actual file storages and their handling in TYPO3.</li> </ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (5, 11, 1706743378, 1706743242, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2080, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Flexform Configuration Data Structure [5]', '', 1, 'flexform-configuration-data-structure-5', 2, '<p>How to create and configure a data structure for my plugin‚Äôs configuration.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>I know how configuration is managed by the ‚Äúplugin‚Äù content type.</li> 	<li>I can provide a custom configuration data structure for my plugin.</li> </ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (6, 11, 1706790679, 1706790100, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2064, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Accessing FlexForm Data [6]', '<p>FlexForm Data can be easily accessed in Controller and passed to fluid template.</p>\r\n<h2>1. In Controller file Classes/Controller/TccdController.php</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\n$this-&gt;view-&gt;assign(\'settings\', $this-&gt;settings);</pre>\r\n<h2>2. In fluid template file Resources/Private/Partials/Tccd/ListAndSearch.html</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;f:comment&gt;[6] - Accessing FlexForm Data&lt;/f:comment&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;\r\n    &lt;f:if condition=\"{settings.singlePid}\"&gt;\r\n        &lt;f:then&gt;\r\n            &lt;f:link.action pageUid=\"{settings.singlePid}\" action=\"show\" arguments=\"{tccd : tccd}\"&gt;{tccd.title}&lt;/f:link.action&gt;\r\n        &lt;/f:then&gt;\r\n        &lt;f:else&gt;\r\n            &lt;f:link.action action=\"show\" arguments=\"{tccd : tccd}\"&gt;{tccd.title}&lt;/f:link.action&gt;\r\n        &lt;/f:else&gt;\r\n    &lt;/f:if&gt;\r\n&lt;/td&gt;</pre>', 1, 'accessing-flexform-data', 2, '<p>Using data provided in FlexForms in plugin CEs and custom records.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Goals</strong></h3>\r\n<ul> 	<li>I know how FlexForm data is stored in the database.&nbsp;</li> 	<li>I can extract data from a FlexForm field.&nbsp;</li> 	<li>I can modify the contents of a FlexForm field.</li> </ul>', '', 2, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (7, 11, 1706792038, 1706791465, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2056, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Database Management System (DBMS) [7]', '<p><strong>TYPO3 relies on storing its data in a relational database management system (RDBMS)</strong>. The&nbsp;Doctrine&nbsp;DBALcomponent is used to enable connecting to different database management systems. Most used is still MySQL / MariaDB, but thanks to Doctrine others like PostgreSQL and SQLite are also an option.</p>\r\n<h2>Using more than 1 database e.g. for special tables is possible</h2>\r\n<p>In file typo3conf/LocalConfigurations.php or typo3conf/Additionalconfiguration.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// [...]\r\n\'DB\' =&gt; [\r\n    \'Connections\' =&gt; [\r\n        \'Default\' =&gt; [\r\n            \'charset\' =&gt; \'utf8\',\r\n            \'dbname\' =&gt; \'default_dbname\',\r\n            \'driver\' =&gt; \'mysqli\',\r\n            \'host\' =&gt; \'default_host\',\r\n            \'password\' =&gt; \'***\',\r\n            \'port\' =&gt; 3306,\r\n            \'user\' =&gt; \'default_user\',\r\n        ],\r\n        \'Syslog\' =&gt; [\r\n            \'charset\' =&gt; \'utf8\',\r\n            \'dbname\' =&gt; \'syslog_dbname\',\r\n            \'driver\' =&gt; \'mysqli\',\r\n            \'host\' =&gt; \'syslog_host\',\r\n            \'password\' =&gt; \'***\',\r\n            \'port\' =&gt; 3306,\r\n            \'user\' =&gt; \'syslog_user\',\r\n        ],\r\n    ],\r\n    \'TableMapping\' =&gt; [\r\n        \'sys_log\' =&gt; \'Syslog\'\r\n    ],\r\n],\r\n// [...]</pre>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>Link</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/Introduction/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/Introduction/Index.html</a></p>', 1, 'database-management-system-dbms-7', 2, '<p>Knowledge about DBMS.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Goals</strong></h3>\r\n<ul> 	<li>I know what a DBMS is and what it is used for.</li> 	<li>I can name some examples.</li> 	<li>I know what the term ‚Äúrelational‚Äù in the context of DBMS means.</li> </ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (8, 11, 1707659370, 1706792178, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2053, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Using the QueryBuilder [8]', '<p>In TYPO3, database queries can be implemented in the MVC model via the repository or manually via the query builder. The query builder is useful if you want to create database queries for tables that do not have a model or if more complex database queries are necessary. INNER and LEFT JOINS can also be implemented using the query builder.</p>\r\n<h2>Hints</h2>\r\n<ul> 	<li>Queries in the&nbsp;query&nbsp;language of Extbase are automatically escaped. In TYPO3 Repositories $this is of type TYPO3\\CMS\\Extbase\\Persistence\\QueryInterface.</li> 	<li>If you use QueryBuilder: Never instantiate and initialize the query builder manually using dependency injection or&nbsp;GeneralUtility::makeInstance(), otherwise you will miss essential dependencies and runtime setup.</li> 	<li>The QueryBuilder holds internal state and must not be reused for different queries. In addition, a reuse comes with a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.derhansen.de/2023/10/the-pitfalls-of-reusing-typo3-querybuilder-analyzing-a-performance-bottleneck.html\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">significant performance penalty and memory consumption</a>.&nbsp;<strong>Use one query builder per query.</strong>&nbsp;Get a fresh one by calling&nbsp;$connection-&gt;createQueryBuilder()&nbsp;if the same table is involved, or use&nbsp;$connectionPool-&gt;getQueryBuilderForTable()&nbsp;for a query to a different table. Do not worry, creating those object instances is quite fast.</li> </ul>\r\n<h2>Implementation</h2>\r\n<h3>In file Classes/Domain/Repository/TccdRepository.php</h3>\r\n<pre>\r\npublic function findAllCategories(): QueryResultInterface|array\r\n{\r\n    // Doctrine DBAL [3]\r\n    // Using the QueryBuilder [8]\r\n    $table = \'sys_category\';\r\n    $queryBuilder = GeneralUtility::makeInstance(ConnectionPool::class)-&gt;getConnectionForTable($table)-&gt;createQueryBuilder();\r\n\r\n    $queryBuilder\r\n        -&gt;select(\'*\')\r\n        -&gt;from($table);\r\n\r\n    $result = $queryBuilder-&gt;executeQuery();\r\n\r\n    while ($row = $result-&gt;fetchAssociative()) {\r\n        $allRows[$row[\'uid\']] = $row;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return $allRows;\r\n}</pre>\r\n<h2>Links</h2>\r\n<ul> 	<li><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/QueryBuilder/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/QueryBuilder/Index.htm</a></li> 	<li><a href=\"https://t3campus.de/typo3-lernen/der-typo3-querybuilder/\">https://t3campus.de/typo3-lernen/der-typo3-querybuilder/</a>&nbsp;(German)</li> </ul>', 1, 'using-the-querybuilder-8', 2, '<p>How to write queries in TYPO3.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Goals</strong></h3>\r\n<ul> 	<li>I know how to use the QueryBuilder built into TYPO3.</li> 	<li>I know how to write a secure query that can target different DBMS.</li> </ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (9, 11, 1707919573, 1706887396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2050, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Using Query Restrictions [9]', '<h2>Implementation</h2>\r\n<h3>In file Classes/Domain/Repository/TccdRepository.php</h3>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Using Query Restrictions [9]\r\nif ((isset($filterParameter[\'showHidden\']) &amp;&amp; $filterParameter[\'showHidden\']) OR\r\n    (isset($filterParameter[\'showDeleted\']) &amp;&amp; $filterParameter[\'showDeleted\'])) {\r\n    $query-&gt;getQuerySettings()-&gt;setIgnoreEnableFields(true);\r\n}\r\nif (isset($filterParameter[\'showDeleted\']) &amp;&amp; $filterParameter[\'showDeleted\']) {\r\n    $query-&gt;getQuerySettings()-&gt;setIncludeDeleted(true);\r\n}\r\nif (isset($filterParameter[\'ignoreStorage\']) &amp;&amp; $filterParameter[\'ignoreStorage\']) {\r\n    $query-&gt;getQuerySettings()-&gt;setRespectStoragePage(false);\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Default restrictions in Repositories</h2>\r\n<ul> 	<li>sys_language_uid IN (0,-1)</li> 	<li>pid = 0</li> 	<li>t3ver_oid =0</li> 	<li>hidden = 0</li> 	<li>deleted = 0</li> 	<li>starttime &lt;= now</li> 	<li>endtime = 0 OR &gt; now</li> </ul>\r\n<h2>Other possible implementations</h2>\r\n<p>Not in Repository but e.g. in Controller with $queryBuilder:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\ConnectionPool;</em>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\Query\\Restriction\\StartTimeRestriction</em>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\Query\\Restriction\\EndTimeRestriction</em>\r\n<em>// Remove starttime and endtime, but keep hidden and deleted</em>\r\n\r\n$queryBuilder = $this-&gt;connectionPool-&gt;getQueryBuilderForTable(\'tt_content\');\r\n$queryBuilder\r\n    -&gt;getRestrictions()\r\n    -&gt;removeByType(StartTimeRestriction::class)\r\n    -&gt;removeByType(EndTimeRestriction::class);</pre>\r\n<p>Or remove all restrictions and then add the ‚Äúdeleted‚Äù restriction:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Utility\\GeneralUtility;\r\n// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\Connection;</em>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\ConnectionPool;</em>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\Query\\Restriction\\DeletedRestriction\r\n</em>\r\n<em>// Remove all restrictions but add DeletedRestriction again</em>\r\n<em>// Result SQL: SELECT `uid`, `bodytext` FROM `tt_content` WHERE (`pid` = 42) AND (`tt_content`.`deleted` = 0)</em>\r\n\r\n$queryBuilder = $this-&gt;connectionPool-&gt;getQueryBuilderForTable(\'tt_content\');\r\n\r\n$queryBuilder\r\n    -&gt;getRestrictions()\r\n    -&gt;removeAll()\r\n    -&gt;add(GeneralUtility::makeInstance(DeletedRestriction::class));\r\n\r\n$result = $queryBuilder\r\n    -&gt;select(\'uid\', \'bodytext\')\r\n    -&gt;from(\'tt_content\')\r\n    -&gt;where($queryBuilder-&gt;expr()-&gt;eq(\r\n        \'pid\',\r\n        $queryBuilder-&gt;createNamedParameter($pid, Connection::PARAM_INT)\r\n    ))\r\n    -&gt;executeQuery()\r\n    -&gt;fetchAllAssociative(();</pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Explanation</h2>\r\n<p>The RestrictionBuilder\'s removeByType() method can also be used to obtain hidden records when using the Query Builder (Doctrine DBAL). ‚ÄúTypes‚Äù are:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>HiddenRestriction</li> 	<li>DeletedRestriction</li> 	<li>StartTimeRestriction</li> 	<li>EndTimeRestriction</li> 	<li>FrontendGroupRestriction</li> </ul>\r\n<p>And can be removed as follows:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>$queryBuilder-&gt;getRestrictions()-&gt;removeByType(HiddenRestriction::class);</li> </ul>\r\n<p>In Extbase repositories, the querysettings setIgnoreEnableFields() and setEnableFieldsToBeIgnored() can be used accordingly to get hidden or deleted elements.</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>$querySettings-&gt;setIgnoreEnableFields(true);</li> 	<li>$querySettings-&gt;setEnableFieldsToBeIgnored([\'deleted\', \'disabled\']);</li> </ul>\r\n<p>To also get deleted items (but not hidden ones), the following method can also be used:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>$querySettings-&gt;setIncludeDeleted(true);</li> </ul>\r\n<p>setIncludeHidden() does not exist.</p>', 1, 'using-query-restrictions-9', 2, '<p>How to restrict database queries.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>I know about the restriction containers applied automatically in TYPO3.</li> 	<li>I know the available restrictions and their usage.</li> 	<li>I know how to change which restrictions are applied.</li> </ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (10, 11, 1707659374, 1706893990, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1921, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'TYPO3 Debugging Utilities [10]', '<h2>Configuration</h2>\r\n<p>In LocalConfiguration.php there are many debug-settings possible:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\nreturn [\r\n   \'BE\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'debug\' =&gt; true,\r\n   ],\r\n   \'FE\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'debug\' =&gt; true,\r\n   ],\r\n   \'SYS\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'devIPmask\' =&gt; \'*\',\r\n      \'displayErrors\' =&gt; 1,\r\n      \'exceptionalErrors\' =&gt; 28674,\r\n   ],\r\n];\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>The following configuration values are of interest:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/BE.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-BE-debug\">$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'BE\'][\'debug\']</a></p>\r\n<p>If enabled, the login refresh is disabled and pageRenderer is set to debug mode. Furthermore the fieldname is appended to the label of fields.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/FE.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-FE-debug\">$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'FE\'][\'debug\']</a></p>\r\n<p>If enabled, the total parse time of the page is added as HTTP response header&nbsp;X-TYPO3-Parsetime.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-devIPmask\">$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'devIPmask\']</a></p>\r\n<p>Defines a list of IP addresses which will allow development output to display. Setting to \"*\" will allow all. Setting it to an empty string allows none.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-displayErrors\">$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'displayErrors\']</a></p>\r\n<p>Configures whether PHP errors or Exceptions should be displayed.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-errorHandler\">$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'errorHandler\']</a></p>\r\n<p>Classname to handle PHP errors. Leave empty to disable error handling.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-errorHandlerErrors\">$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'errorHandlerErrors\']</a></p>\r\n<p>The&nbsp;E_*&nbsp;constants that will be handled by the error handler.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-exceptionalErrors\">$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'exceptionalErrors\']</a></p>\r\n<p>The&nbsp;E_*&nbsp;constant that will be converted into an exception by the default errorHandler.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-productionExceptionHandler\">$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'productionExceptionHandler\']</a></p>\r\n<p>The default exception handler displays a nice error message when something goes wrong. The error message is logged to the configured logs.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-debugExceptionHandler\">$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'debugExceptionHandler\']</a></p>\r\n<p>The default debug exception handler displays the complete stack trace of any encountered exception. The error message and the stack trace is logged to the configured logs.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-belogErrorReporting\">$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'belogErrorReporting\']</a></p>\r\n<p>Configures which PHP errors should be logged to the&nbsp;sys_log&nbsp;table.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Frontend Debug</h2>\r\n<ul> 	<li>In PHP code: print_r, echo, var_dump(), debug(),&nbsp;DebugUtility::debug</li> </ul>\r\n<pre>\r\n\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Utility\\DebugUtility::debug($filterParameter, \'filterParameter\');</pre>\r\n<ul> 	<li>In Frontend: AdminPanel</li> 	<li>In TypoScript or EXT:some_extension/Configuration/TypoScript/setup.typoscript</li> </ul>\r\n<pre>\r\nconfig.contentObjectExceptionHandler = 0\r\n</pre>\r\n<h2>Backend Debug</h2>\r\n<p>To display additional debug information in the backend, set&nbsp;$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'BE\'][\'debug\'] in LocalConfiguration.php and log in with an administrator account.</p>\r\n<h2>SQL Debug</h2>\r\n<p>It can be very helpful to debug the final statements of queryBuilder with debug($queryBuilder-&gt;getSQL())</p>\r\n<h2>Good to know</h2>\r\n<p>In debug mode, the page renderer does not compress or concatenate JavaScript or CSS resources.</p>\r\n<h2>Links</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/ErrorAndExceptionHandling/Configuration/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/ErrorAndExceptionHandling/Configuration/Index.html</a><br /> <a href=\"https://www.php.net/manual/en/errorfunc.constants.php\">https://www.php.net/manual/en/errorfunc.constants.php</a></p>', 1, 'typo3-debugging-utilities', 2, '<p>Knowledge about debugging utilities provided by TYPO3.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>I know the built-in mechanics to output debug messages:&nbsp; 	<ul> 		<li>Extbase DebuggerUtility</li> 		<li>DebugUtility</li> 		<li>admin panel</li> 	</ul> 	</li> 	<li>I know how to add debug output to the frontend.</li> 	<li>I know how to add debug output to the backend.</li> </ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (11, 11, 1707651750, 1706992174, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1793, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tracing Errors in Logs [11]', '<h2>Log files (Goal 1)</h2>\r\n<ol> 	<li>PHP - Logfile</li> 	<li>Apache (or Nginx) logfile</li> 	<li>Mysql Logfile</li> 	<li>TYPO3 logfile (Default: typo3temp/var/log/)</li> 	<li>TYPO3 deprecation logfile&nbsp;(Default: typo3temp/var/log/)</li> </ol>\r\n<p>For MAMP 1-3 are saved in MAMP/logs/</p>\r\n<h2>Database Logtable&nbsp; (Goal 1)</h2>\r\n<ul> 	<li>sys_log (TYPO3 Backend / System / Log)</li> </ul>\r\n<h2>Adminpanel (Goal 1)</h2>\r\n<h2>ErrorHandler</h2>\r\n<p>The ErrorHandler (\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Error\\ErrorHandler) has the following functions</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>Displays error messages as flash messages in the backend (if ExceptionHandler is set to \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Error\\DebugExceptionHandler)</li> 	<li>Displays errors as TsLog messages in the admin panel.</li> 	<li>Logs error messages via the logging API.</li> 	<li>Logs error messages in the sys_log table. Logged errors are displayed in the Belog extension (Administration Tools &gt; Log).</li> </ul>\r\n<h2>TYPO3 Logging</h2>\r\n<p>Codes for Logging framework are</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>0 Emergency</li> 	<li>1 Alert</li> 	<li>2 Critical</li> 	<li>3 Error</li> 	<li>4 Warning</li> 	<li>5 Notice</li> 	<li>6 Informational</li> 	<li>7 Debug</li> </ul>\r\n<h2>Configuration (Goal 2)</h2>\r\n<p>In LocalConfiguration.php there are many debug-settings possible:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\nreturn [\r\n   \'BE\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'debug\' =&gt; true,\r\n   ],\r\n   \'FE\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'debug\' =&gt; true,\r\n   ],\r\n   \'SYS\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'devIPmask\' =&gt; \'*\', // Goal 3\r\n      \'displayErrors\' =&gt; 1,\r\n      \'exceptionalErrors\' =&gt; 28674,\r\n   ],\r\n];\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>Table: SYS Configuration</p>\r\n<table> 	<thead> 		<tr> 			<th> 			<p>Key</p> 			</th> 			<th> 			<p>Data type</p> 			</th> 			<th> 			<p>Description</p> 			</th> 		</tr> 	</thead> 	<tbody> 		<tr> 			<td> 			<p>displayErrors</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>integer</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>Configures whether PHP errors should be displayed.</p> 			<ul> 				<li> 				<p>0 = Do not display any PHP error messages. Overrides the value of \"exceptionalErrors\" and sets it to 0 (= no errors are turned into exceptions),the configured&nbsp;productionExceptionHandler&nbsp;is used as exception handler</p> 				</li> 				<li> 				<p>1 = Display error messages with the registered error handler, the configured&nbsp;debugExceptionHandler&nbsp;is used as exception handler</p> 				</li> 				<li> 				<p>-1 = Default setting. With this option, you can override the PHP setting&nbsp;display_errors. If&nbsp;devIPmask&nbsp;matches the users IP address the configured&nbsp;debugExceptionHandler&nbsp;is used for exceptions, if not&nbsp;productionExceptionHandler&nbsp;will be used.</p> 				</li> 			</ul> 			</td> 		</tr> 		<tr> 			<td> 			<p>errorHandler</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>string</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>Classname to handle PHP errors. Leave empty to disable error handling.</p> 			<p>Default:&nbsp;\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Error\\ErrorHandler. This class will register itself as error handler. It is able to write error messages to all available logging systems in TYPO3. See&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/Logging/Index.html#logging\">Logging Framework</a>for more.</p> 			<p>Additionally the errors can be displayed as flash messages in the Backend or in the adminpanel in Frontend. The flash messages in Backend are only displayed if the error and exception handling is in \"debug-mode\", which is the case when the configured \"debugExceptionHandler\" is registered as exception handler (see:$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'displayErrors\']).</p> 			<p>Errors which are registered as \"exceptionalErrors\" will be turned into exceptions (to be handled by the configured exceptionHandler).</p> 			</td> 		</tr> 		<tr> 			<td> 			<p>errorHandlerErrors</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>integer</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>The&nbsp;E_*&nbsp;constant that will be handled by the error handler</p> 			<p>Default:&nbsp;E_ALL&nbsp;^&nbsp;E_NOTICE</p> 			</td> 		</tr> 		<tr> 			<td> 			<p>exceptionalErrors</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>integer</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>The&nbsp;E_*&nbsp;constant that will be handled as an exception by the error handler.</p> 			<p>Default:&nbsp;E_ALL&nbsp;^&nbsp;E_NOTICE&nbsp;^&nbsp;E_WARNING&nbsp;^&nbsp;E_USER_ERROR&nbsp;^E_USER_NOTICE&nbsp;^&nbsp;E_USER_WARNING&nbsp;(4341) and \"0\" if&nbsp;$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'displayErrors\']&nbsp;=&nbsp;0.</p> 			<p>Refer to the PHP documentation for more details on this value.</p> 			</td> 		</tr> 		<tr> 			<td> 			<p>productionExceptionHandler</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>string</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>Classname to handle exceptions that might happen in the TYPO3-code.</p> 			<p>Leave empty to disable exception handling.</p> 			<p>Default:&nbsp;\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Error\\ProductionExceptionHandler. This exception handler displays a nice error message when something went wrong. The error message is logged to the configured logs.</p> 			<p>Note</p> 			<p>The configured productionExceptionHandler is used if$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'displayErrors\']&nbsp;is set to \"0\" or to \"-1\" and&nbsp;$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'devIPmask\']&nbsp;doesn\'t match.</p> 			</td> 		</tr> 		<tr> 			<td> 			<p>debugExceptionHandler</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>string</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>Classname to handle exceptions that might happen in the TYPO3 code.</p> 			<p>Leave empty to disable exception handling.</p> 			<p>Default:&nbsp;\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Error\\DebugExceptionHandler. This exception handler displays the complete stack trace of any encountered exception. The error message and the stack trace is logged to the configured logs.</p> 			<p>Note</p> 			<p>The configured debugExceptionHandler is used if$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'displayErrors\']&nbsp;is set to \"1\" or if&nbsp;$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'displayErrors\']&nbsp;is \"-1\" or \"2\" and the&nbsp;$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'devIPmask\']matches.</p> 			</td> 		</tr> 		<tr> 			<td> 			<p>belogErrorReporting</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>integer</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>Configures which PHP errors should be logged to the \"sys_log\" table (extension: belog). If set to \"0\" no PHP errors are logged to the \"sys_log\" table.</p> 			<p>Default:&nbsp;E_ALL&nbsp;^&nbsp;E_NOTICE&nbsp;(6135).</p> 			</td> 		</tr> 	</tbody> </table>\r\n<p>Table: displayErrors</p>\r\n<table> 	<thead> 		<tr> 			<th> 			<p>displayErrors</p> 			</th> 			<th> 			<p>errorHandlerErrors</p> 			</th> 			<th> 			<p>exceptionalErrors</p> 			</th> 			<th> 			<p>errorHandler</p> 			</th> 			<th> 			<p>devIPmask</p> 			</th> 			<th> 			<p>exceptionHandler</p> 			</th> 			<th> 			<p>display_errors</p> 			<p>(php_ini)</p> 			</th> 		</tr> 	</thead> 	<tbody> 		<tr> 			<td rowspan=\"2\"> 			<p>-1</p> 			</td> 			<td rowspan=\"2\"> 			<p>E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE</p> 			</td> 			<td rowspan=\"2\"> 			<p>E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE ^ E_WARNING ^ E_USER_ERROR ^ E_USER_NOTICE</p> 			</td> 			<td rowspan=\"2\"> 			<p>TYPO3CMS CoreError ErrorHandler</p> 			</td> 			<td rowspan=\"2\"> 			<p>Matters</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>If devIPmask matches: debugExceptionHandler</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>Not changed</p> 			</td> 		</tr> 		<tr> 			<td> 			<p>If devIPmask doesn\'t match: productionExceptionHandler</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>Not changed</p> 			</td> 		</tr> 		<tr> 			<td> 			<p>0</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p><strong>0</strong>&nbsp;<strong>(no errors are turned into exceptions)</strong></p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>TYPO3CMS CoreError ErrorHandler</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>Doesn\'t matter</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>production ExceptionHandler</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p><strong>0 (Off)</strong></p> 			</td> 		</tr> 		<tr> 			<td> 			<p>1</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE ^ E_WARNING ^ E_USER_ERROR ^ E_USER_NOTICE ^ E_USER_WARNING</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>TYPO3CMS CoreError ErrorHandler</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>Doesn\'t matter</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p>debugException Handler</p> 			</td> 			<td> 			<p><strong>1 (On)</strong></p> 			</td> 		</tr> 	</tbody> </table>\r\n<p>See TYPO3 v10 Documentation (but mostly valid for TYPO3 v11):<br /> <a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/ErrorAndExceptionHandling/Configuration/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/ErrorAndExceptionHandling/Configuration/Index.html</a></p>\r\n\r\n', 1, 'tracing-errors-in-logs-11', 3, '<p>Knowledge about log sources and how to utilize them in order to resolve errors.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>I know where to look when my instance throws error messages or white pages.</li> 	<li>I know which configuration options define the error output of TYPO3 and Extbase.</li> 	<li>I know how to limit error output to development machines or certain IPs on live instances.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (12, 11, 1707383996, 1707311046, 0, 0, 0, 0, 512, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Logging API [12]', '<p>Logging API follows <strong>PSR-3.</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">All log writers can be used in your own classes. If the service is configured to use autowiring (in Configuration/Services.yaml) you can inject a logger into the&nbsp;__construct()&nbsp;method of your class&nbsp;\\MyVendor\\MyExtension\\MyFolder\\MyClass) since TYPO3 v11 LTS as follows:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\ndeclare(strict_types=1);\r\n\r\nnamespace MyVendor\\MyExtension;\r\n\r\nuse Psr\\Log\\LoggerInterface;\r\n\r\nclass MyClass\r\n{\r\n    public function __construct(\r\n        private readonly LoggerInterface $logger,\r\n    ) {\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>Outputs to the log file are generated as follows:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n$this-&gt;logger-&gt;error(\'Passing {value} was unwise.\', [    \r\n    \'value\' =&gt; $value,\r\n    \'other_data\' =&gt; $foo,\r\n]);</pre>\r\n<p>$this-&gt;logger-&gt;warning, or critical is&nbsp;also possible</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, logger-&gt;log can also be called with LogLevel:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n$this-&gt;logger-&gt;log(LogLevel::CRITICAL, \'This is an utter failure!\');</pre>\r\n<p>Codes for Logging Framework are</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li> 	<p>0 Emergency</p> 	</li> 	<li> 	<p>1 Alert</p> 	</li> 	<li> 	<p>2 Critical</p> 	</li> 	<li> 	<p>3 Error</p> 	</li> 	<li> 	<p>4 Warning</p> 	</li> 	<li> 	<p>5 Notice</p> 	</li> 	<li> 	<p>6 Informational</p> 	</li> 	<li> 	<p>7 Debug</p> 	</li> </ul>\r\n<h2>Implementation</h2>\r\n<p>If you call the detail (/tccd/detail/) view of this extension with no parameters you are redirected to the list page. For testing purposes \"Detail view called without parameter\" is written to the log, or in complete:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\nThu, 08 Feb 2024 10:11:26 +0100 [WARNING] request=\"26e20ee8d9732\" component=\"Machwert.TccdExamples.Controller.TccdController\": Detail view called without parameter </pre>', 1, 'logging-api-12', 2, '<p>Knowledge about the logging API provided by TYPO3.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>I know how to compose a proper log message and of which parts it consists.</li> 	<li>I know about the different log levels and their meaning.</li> 	<li>I know how to get and use a logger in my code.</li> 	<li>I know about log channels and how to use them in my code.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (13, 11, 1707651656, 1707384210, 0, 0, 0, 0, 256, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Debugging in PHP [13]', '<h2>Goal 2</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.machwert.de/tipps-und-tricks/tipp/xdebug-phpstorm-und-typo3/\">https://www.machwert.de/tipps-und-tricks/tipp/xdebug-phpstorm-und-typo3/</a></p>', 1, 'debugging-in-php-13', 2, '<p>Basic knowledge about error tracing methods in PHP.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>I know about simple methods to print values to output (var_dump, print_r, echo, die).</li> 	<li>I know how to set up and use a debugging tool like Xdebug.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', '');
INSERT INTO `tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd` (`uid`, `pid`, `tstamp`, `crdate`, `deleted`, `hidden`, `starttime`, `endtime`, `sorting`, `sys_language_uid`, `l10n_parent`, `l10n_state`, `l10n_diffsource`, `t3ver_oid`, `t3ver_wsid`, `t3ver_state`, `t3ver_stage`, `title`, `description`, `version`, `slug`, `categories`, `syllabusdescription`, `link`, `edited`, `images`, `makenewtranslation`, `related_tccds`, `links`) VALUES
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (14, 11, 1707653628, 1707651835, 0, 0, 0, 0, 128, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Knowledge about Environment Error Logs [14]', '<h2>TYPO3 Logfiles</h2>\r\n<p>TYPO3 Log Configuration ist set in <strong>$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'LOG\']</strong> and normally set in typo3conf/LocalConfiguration.php or typo3conf/AdditionalConfiguration.php.</p>\r\n<p>Default TYPO3 Error logfile directory is <strong>typo3temp/var/log/</strong></p>\r\n<p>TYPO3 Logifle can be accessed in TYPO3 Backend in <strong>System / Log</strong><br /> TYPO3 Deprecation logfile can be accessed only directly in file system</p>\r\n<p>Codes for Logging Framework are</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>0 Emergency</li> 	<li>1 Alert</li> 	<li>2 Critical</li> 	<li>3 Error</li> 	<li>4 Warning</li> 	<li>5 Notice</li> 	<li>6 Informational</li> 	<li>7 Debug</li> </ul>\r\n<h2><br /> Webserver (Apache or Nginx) and PHP Logfiles</h2>\r\n<p>For MAMP Installations log files are safed in <strong>MAMP/logs</strong></p>\r\n<p>Here you find</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>php_error.log</li> 	<li>apache_error.log (or nginx_error.log)</li> 	<li>mysql_error.log</li> </ul>\r\n<p>For linux distributions they are mostly located in <strong>var/log</strong></p>\r\n\r\n', 1, 'knowledge-about-environment-error-logs-14', 2, '<p>Ability to locate logs provided by system components.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>I know where the error logs of TYPO3, a web server and PHP are located.</li> 	<li>I can access these logs in order to trace errors occurring in my environment. &nbsp;</li> 	<li>I know how to interpret error log messages in order to resolve the error.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (15, 11, 1707999327, 1707655425, 0, 0, 0, 0, 64, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'PSR-7: Request/Response [15]', '<p>The&nbsp;PSR-7&nbsp;based request object is available in most contexts. In some scenarios, like&nbsp;PSR-15 middlewares&nbsp;or backend module controllers, the PSR-7 base request object is given as argument to the called method.</p>\r\n<p>in an&nbsp;<strong>Extbase controller</strong>&nbsp;the request object compatible with the&nbsp;PSR-7&nbsp;\\Psr\\Http\\Message\\ServerRequestInterface&nbsp;is available via the class property&nbsp;$this-&gt;request.</p>\r\n<p>In a <strong>ViewHelper</strong> you can get the rendering request from the rendering context.</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\n\r\ndeclare(strict_types=1);\r\n\r\nnamespace MyVendor\\MyExtension\\ViewHelpers;\r\n\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Fluid\\Core\\Rendering\\RenderingContext;\r\nuse TYPO3Fluid\\Fluid\\Core\\Rendering\\RenderingContextInterface;\r\nuse TYPO3Fluid\\Fluid\\Core\\ViewHelper\\AbstractViewHelper;\r\n\r\nfinal class MyViewHelper extends AbstractViewHelper\r\n{\r\n    public static function renderStatic(array $arguments, \\Closure $renderChildrenClosure, RenderingContextInterface $renderingContext): string\r\n    {\r\n        /** @var RenderingContext $renderingContext */\r\n        $request = $renderingContext-&gt;getRequest();\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>In a&nbsp;<strong>TypoScript user function</strong>&nbsp;the request object is available as third parameter of the called class method.</p>\r\n<p>A&nbsp;<strong>data processor</strong>&nbsp;receives a reference to the&nbsp;\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Frontend\\ContentObject\\ContentObjectRenderer&nbsp;as first argument for the&nbsp;process()&nbsp;method. This object provides a&nbsp;getRequest()&nbsp;method.</p>\r\n<p>TYPO3 provides the request object also in the global variable&nbsp;<strong>$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_REQUEST\']</strong>. If possible don\'t use it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Attributes</h3>\r\n<p>Attributes enriches the request with further information. TYPO3 provides attributes which can be used in custom implementations.</p>\r\n<p>The attributes can be retrieved via</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Get all available attributes\r\n$allAttributes = $request-&gt;getAttributes();\r\n\r\n// Get only a specific attribute, here the site entity in frontend context\r\n$site = $request-&gt;getAttribute(\'site\');\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>The following attributes are available in frontend context:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>Application type</li> 	<li>Frontend controller</li> 	<li>Frontend user</li> 	<li>Language</li> 	<li>Normalized parameters</li> 	<li>Routing</li> 	<li>Site</li> </ul>\r\n<p>The following attributes are available in backend context:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>Application type</li> 	<li>Normalized parameters</li> 	<li>Route</li> 	<li>Site</li> 	<li>Target</li> </ul>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/RequestLifeCycle/Typo3Request.html?highlight=psr%207\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/RequestLifeCycle/Typo3Request.html?highlight=psr%207</a></p>', 1, 'psr-7-requestresponse-15', 1, '<p>This skill covers the PSR standard for HTTP request/response objects.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>I have basic knowledge about the standard PSR-7.</li> 	<li>I know how to deal with request and response objects in PHP.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (16, 11, 1710506348, 1707657405, 0, 0, 0, 0, 32, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Extending Existing Functionality [16]', '<h3>1. Hooks (Goal 1)</h3>\r\n<p>A hook is an ‚Äúinterruption‚Äù at a given point in the current program flow in order to then incorporate code from a completely different source.</p>\r\n<p>There are two types of hooks. Firstly, the hooks with which you can extend certain functions with further functionality and secondly, hooks with which you can change content.</p>\r\n<p>If possible prefer PSR-14 events.</p>\r\n<h4>1-1. Implementation using hooks</h4>\r\n<p>1. File ext_localconf.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Extending Existing Functionality [16] - Hooks\r\n$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SC_OPTIONS\'][\'t3lib/class.t3lib_tcemain.php\'][\'processDatamapClass\'][\'tccd_examples\']\r\n    = \\Machwert\\TccdExamples\\Hooks\\MyDataHandlerHooks::class;</pre>\r\n<p>2. File Classes/Hooks/MyDataHandlerHooks.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\nnamespace Machwert\\TccdExamples\\Hooks;\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\DataHandling\\DataHandler;\r\n\r\n// source: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/74543820/updating-data-after-backend-action-typo3-11-5\r\n\r\n// Extending Existing Functionality [16] - Hooks\r\n\r\nclass MyDataHandlerHooks {\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * @param string|int $id\r\n     */\r\n    public function processDatamap_postProcessFieldArray(\r\n        string $status,         // Status of the current operation, \'new\' or \'update\'\r\n        string $table,          // The table currently processing data for\r\n               $id,             // The record uid currently processing data for,\r\n                                // [integer] or [string] (like \'NEW...\')\r\n        array &amp;$fieldArray,     // The field array of a record, cleaned to only\r\n                                // \'to-be-changed\' values. Needs to be &amp;$fieldArray to be considered reference.\r\n        DataHandler $dataHandler\r\n    ): void\r\n    {\r\n        // $fieldArray may be stripped down to only the real fields which\r\n        // needs to be updated, mainly for $status === \'update\'. So if you\r\n        // need to be sure to have correct data you may have to retrieve\r\n        // the record to get the current value, if not provided as with new\r\n        // value.\r\n\r\n        if ($table === \'tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd\'\r\n            &amp;&amp; $status === \'update\'\r\n            &amp;&amp; array_key_exists(\'title\', $fieldArray)\r\n        ) {\r\n            $valueToReactTo = $fieldArray[\'title\'];\r\n            if ($valueToReactTo === \'Test Datahandler Hook\') {\r\n                $fieldArray[\'description\'] = \'Test Datahandler Hook Description\';\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p><strong>Test Implementation</strong></p>\r\n<p>Set in \"Test Datahandler Hook\" as title for new Syllabus-Dataset of this extension.<br /> The Description will be filled with \"Test Datahandler Hook Description\" automatically after saving.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. PSR-14 events (Goal 2)</h3>\r\n<h4>2-1. &nbsp;Implementation of using existing PSR-14 events:</h4>\r\n<p><strong>Usecase:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Remove hreflang-tag if dataset is not translated</p>\r\n<p>File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Configuration/Services.yaml:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\nMachwert\\TccdExamples\\EventListener\\OwnHrefLang: # Extending Existing Functionality [16] - PSR-14 events (Goal 2)\r\n  tags:\r\n    - name: event.listener\r\n      identifier: \'tccdExamples/ownHrefLang\'\r\n      after: \'typo3-seo/hreflangGenerator\'\r\n      event: TYPO3\\CMS\\Frontend\\Event\\ModifyHrefLangTagsEvent</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>File:&nbsp;typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Classes/EventListener/OwnHrefLang.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\n\r\nnamespace Machwert\\TccdExamples\\EventListener;\r\n\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\Connection;\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\ConnectionPool;\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Utility\\GeneralUtility;\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Frontend\\Event\\ModifyHrefLangTagsEvent;\r\n\r\n# Extending Existing Functionality [16] - PSR-14 events (Goal 2)\r\n\r\nclass OwnHrefLang\r\n{\r\n    public function __invoke(ModifyHrefLangTagsEvent $event): void\r\n    {\r\n        $hrefLangs = $event-&gt;getHrefLangs();\r\n        $request = $event-&gt;getRequest();\r\n        $hrefLangModified = false;\r\n\r\n        $queryParams = ($request-&gt;getQueryParams());\r\n        $tccdUid = $queryParams[\'tx_tccdexamples_tccdpluginshow\'][\'tccd\'] ?? 0;\r\n        $tccdUid = (int)$tccdUid;\r\n\r\n        if ($tccdUid &gt; 0) {\r\n            $siteLanguages = $request-&gt;getAttribute(\'site\')-&gt;getLanguages();\r\n            foreach($siteLanguages as $key =&gt; $val) {\r\n                if ($val-&gt;getLanguageId() &gt; 0) {\r\n                    // check if translation exists\r\n                    // SELECT uid FROM tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd WHERE l10n_parent = $tccdUid AND sys_language_uid = $val-&gt;getLanguageId()\r\n\r\n                    $notfound = true;\r\n                    $tableName = \'tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd\';\r\n                    $queryBuilder = GeneralUtility::makeInstance(ConnectionPool::class)-&gt;getConnectionForTable($tableName)-&gt;createQueryBuilder();\r\n\r\n                    $queryBuilder\r\n                        -&gt;select(\'uid\')\r\n                        -&gt;from($tableName)\r\n                        -&gt;where(\r\n                            $queryBuilder-&gt;expr()-&gt;eq(\'l10n_parent\', $queryBuilder-&gt;createNamedParameter($tccdUid, Connection::PARAM_INT)),\r\n                            $queryBuilder-&gt;expr()-&gt;eq(\'sys_language_uid\', $queryBuilder-&gt;createNamedParameter($val-&gt;getLanguageId(), Connection::PARAM_INT)),\r\n                        );\r\n\r\n                    $result = $queryBuilder-&gt;executeQuery();\r\n\r\n                    while ($row = $result-&gt;fetchAssociative()) {\r\n                        $notfound = false;\r\n                    }\r\n\r\n                    if($notfound) {\r\n                        unset($hrefLangs[$val-&gt;getHreflang()]);\r\n                        $hrefLangModified = true;\r\n                    }\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n            if ($hrefLangModified) {\r\n                $event-&gt;setHrefLangs($hrefLangs);\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<h4>2-2. Implementation of creating PSR-14 event</h4>\r\n<p>Use case: Modify page title in dataset detail view and make it availabe as an event, so it can be changed by others easily</p>\r\n<p>File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Classes/Controller/TccdController.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n# Extending Existing Functionality [16] - PSR-14 events (Goal 2) - start\r\n$modifyPagetitleEvent = new ModifyPagetitleEvent();\r\n$this-&gt;eventDispatcher-&gt;dispatch($modifyPagetitleEvent);\r\n$modifyPagetitleEvent-&gt;setTccdExamplesPagetitle($tccd-&gt;getTitle());\r\n# end</pre>\r\n<p>File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Classes/Event/ModifyPagetitleEvent.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\n\r\ndeclare(strict_types=1);\r\n\r\nnamespace Machwert\\TccdExamples\\Event;\r\n\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\MetaTag\\MetaTagManagerRegistry;\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Utility\\GeneralUtility;\r\n\r\n# Extending Existing Functionality [16] - PSR-14 events (Goal 2)\r\n\r\nfinal class ModifyPagetitleEvent\r\n{\r\n    public function __construct(\r\n    ) {}\r\n\r\n    public function setTccdExamplesPagetitle($pageTitle) {\r\n        $GLOBALS[\'TSFE\']-&gt;indexedDocTitle = $pageTitle;\r\n        $titleProvider = GeneralUtility::makeInstance(\\Machwert\\TccdExamples\\PageTitle\\MyRecordTitleProvider::class);\r\n        $titleProvider-&gt;setTitle($pageTitle);\r\n\r\n        // set og:title\r\n        $metaTagManager = GeneralUtility::makeInstance(MetaTagManagerRegistry::class)-&gt;getManagerForProperty(\'og:title\');\r\n        $metaTagManager-&gt;addProperty(\'og:title\', $pageTitle);\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. UserFunctions</h3>\r\n<h4>3-1 UserFunctions in general</h4>\r\n<p>Use case: Display last cached Date and Time</p>\r\n<p>File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Configuration/TypoScript/setup.typoscript</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n#Extending Existing Functionality [16] - 3. UserFunctions\r\npage.1010 = USER\r\npage.1010 {\r\n    userFunc = Machwert\\TccdExamples\\UserFunctions\\CachedTime-&gt;printTime\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Classes/UserFunctions/CachedTime.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\ndeclare(strict_types=1);\r\nnamespace Machwert\\TccdExamples\\UserFunctions;\r\n\r\n#Extending Existing Functionality [16] - 3. UserFunctions\r\n\r\nfinal class CachedTime {\r\n    /**\r\n     * Output the current time in red letters\r\n     *\r\n     * @param string          Empty string (no content to process)\r\n     * @param array           TypoScript configuration\r\n     * @return        string          HTML output, showing the current server time.\r\n     */\r\n    public function printTime(string $content, array $conf): string\r\n    {\r\n        return \'&lt;div class=\"outer\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Last cached: \' . date(\'Y-m-d H:i:s\') . \'&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\';\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n<h4>3-2. userFuncs in the TCA</h4>\r\n<p>Use case: Implement multiple links in one TCA field&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3-2-1 File typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/ext_localconf.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n# Extending Existing Functionality [16] - 3-2 userFuncs in the TCA\r\n$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'formEngine\'][\'nodeRegistry\'][1709773998] = [\r\n    \'nodeName\' =&gt; \'specialLinkfieldElement\',\r\n    \'priority\' =&gt; 40,\r\n    \'class\' =&gt; \\Machwert\\TccdExamples\\Form\\Element\\SpecialLinkfieldElement::class,\r\n];</pre>\r\n<p>3-2-2. File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Configuration/TCA/tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n# Extending Existing Functionality [16] - 3-2 userFuncs in the TCA\r\n\'links\' =&gt; [\r\n    \'exclude\' =&gt; true,\r\n    \'label\' =&gt; \'LLL:EXT:tccd_examples/Resources/Private/Language/locallang_db.xlf:tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd.links\',\r\n    \'config\' =&gt; [\r\n        \'type\' =&gt; \'user\',\r\n        \'renderType\' =&gt; \'specialLinkfieldElement\',\r\n    ]\r\n],</pre>\r\n<p>3-2-3. File:&nbsp;typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Classes/Form/Element/SpecialLinkfieldElement.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\ndeclare(strict_types = 1);\r\nnamespace Machwert\\TccdExamples\\Form\\Element;\r\n\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Backend\\Form\\Element\\AbstractFormElement;\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Backend\\Form\\Element\\InputLinkElement;\r\n\r\n# Extending Existing Functionality [16] - 3-2 userFuncs in the TCA\r\n\r\nclass SpecialLinkfieldElement extends AbstractFormElement\r\n{\r\n\r\n    public function render():array\r\n    {\r\n        $htmlAdd = \'\';\r\n        $parameterArray = $this-&gt;data[\'parameterArray\'];\r\n        $itemFormElName = $parameterArray[\'itemFormElName\'];\r\n        $itemValue = $parameterArray[\'itemFormElValue\'];\r\n\r\n        if($itemValue != \'\') {\r\n            $itemValue .= \',\';\r\n        }\r\n        $itemValueArray = explode(\",\", $itemValue);\r\n\r\n        $newData = $this-&gt;data;\r\n\r\n        foreach($itemValueArray as $key =&gt; $val) {\r\n            $newData[\'parameterArray\'][\'itemFormElValue\'] = $val;\r\n            if ($key &gt; 0) {\r\n                $newId = 10500 + $key;\r\n                $newData[\'parameterArray\'][\'itemFormElName\'] = \'data[tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd][\'.$newId.\'][links]\';\r\n                $newData[\'parameterArray\'][\'itemFormElID\'] = \'data_tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd_\'.$newId.\'_links\';\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            $inputLinkElement2 = new InputLinkElement($this-&gt;nodeFactory, $newData);\r\n            $resultArray2 = $inputLinkElement2-&gt;render();\r\n\r\n            if ($key == 0) {\r\n                $resultArray = $resultArray2;\r\n            } else {\r\n                preg_match_all(\'/id=\"([^\"]+)\"/\', $resultArray2[\'html\'], $matches);\r\n                $idArray = $matches[1];\r\n                foreach ($idArray as $id) {\r\n                    if (strpos($id, \'t3js-formengine-\') === 0) {\r\n                        $resultArray[\'requireJsModules\'][0]-&gt;instance(\'#\'.$id);\r\n                    }\r\n                    if (strpos($id, \'formengine-input-\') === 0) {\r\n                        $resultArray[\'requireJsModules\'][1]-&gt;instance($id);\r\n                    }\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            $htmlAdd .= $resultArray2[\'html\'];\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        $htmlAdd .= \"\r\n        &lt;script&gt;\r\n     \r\n        var button = document.querySelector(\'button[name=\\\"_savedok\\\"]\');\r\n\r\n        button.addEventListener(\'click\', function(event) {\r\n            var inputElements = document.querySelectorAll(\'input[name^=\\\"data[tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd][\\\"][name$=\\\"][links]\\\"], input[data-formengine-input-name^=\\\"data[tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd][\\\"][data-formengine-input-name$=\\\"][links]\\\"]\');\r\n            //var inputElements = document.querySelectorAll(\'input[name^=\\\"data[tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd][\\\"][name$=\\\"][links]\\\"]\');\r\n\r\n            var values = [];\r\n            \r\n            inputElements.forEach(function(input) {\r\n                if (input.value &amp;&amp; !values.includes(input.value)) {\r\n                    values.push(input.value);\r\n                }\r\n                \r\n                input.value = \'\';\r\n                \r\n                if (input.name != \'\".$itemFormElName.\"\') {\r\n                    input.remove();\r\n                }\r\n                \r\n                var previousInput = findPreviousInput(input);\r\n                if (previousInput) {\r\n                    previousInput.value = \'\';\r\n                }\r\n                \r\n            });\r\n            \r\n            var commaSeparatedString = values.join(\',\');\r\n            if (commaSeparatedString.endsWith(\',\')) {\r\n                commaSeparatedString = commaSeparatedString.slice(0, -1);\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            var targetInput = document.querySelector(\'input[name=\\\"\".$itemFormElName.\"\\\"]\');\r\n            if (targetInput) {\r\n                targetInput.value = commaSeparatedString;\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            // event.preventDefault();\r\n        });\r\n        \r\n        function findPreviousInput(element) {\r\n            var previousSibling = element.previousElementSibling;\r\n            while (previousSibling) {\r\n                if (previousSibling.classList.contains(\'t3js-form-field-inputlink-explanation\') &amp;&amp; previousSibling.tagName.toLowerCase() === \'input\') {\r\n                    return previousSibling;\r\n                }\r\n                previousSibling = previousSibling.previousElementSibling;\r\n            }\r\n            return null;\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n        &lt;/script&gt;\r\n        \";\r\n\r\n        $resultArray[\'html\'] = $htmlAdd;\r\n        return $resultArray;\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>', 1, 'extending-existing-functionality-16', 1, '<p>Extending core and extension functionality without changing code.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>I know what hooks are and the two different types of hook implementations.</li> 	<li>I know about PSR-14 events and how they are implemented in TYPO3.</li> 	<li>I know what userFuncs in the TCA are and how to take advantage of them.</li> 	<li>I can identify places where TYPO3 allows to extend built-in functionality.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (17, 11, 1710757492, 1707678889, 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'PSR-3: Logger Interface standard [17]', '<h3>Goal 1: LoggerInterface</h3>\r\n<ul> 	<li> 	<p>The&nbsp;LoggerInterface&nbsp;exposes eight methods to write logs to the eight&nbsp;<a href=\"http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5424\">RFC 5424</a>&nbsp;levels (debug, info, notice, warning, error, critical, alert, emergency).</p> 	</li> 	<li> 	<p>A ninth method,&nbsp;log, accepts a log level as the first argument.&nbsp;</p> 	</li> 	<li> 	<p><a href=\"https://www.php-fig.org/psr/psr-3/\">https://www.php-fig.org/psr/psr-3/</a></p> 	</li> </ul>\r\n<h3><br /> Goal 2: Standard implementations of PSR-3</h3>\r\n<ul> 	<li>In TYPO3 Controller: LoggerInferface ist implemented by constructor injection</li> </ul>\r\n<h3><br /> Goal 3:&nbsp;API methods of PSR-3 LoggerInterface</h3>\r\n<ul> 	<li>LoggerInferace methods:&nbsp;(debug, info, notice, warning, error, critical, alert, emergency, log</li> 	<li>LoggerAwareInterface method: setLogger</li> </ul>\r\n<h3><br /> Goal 4: PSR-3-based logging in my own extension</h3>\r\n<p>In file: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Classes/Controller/TccdController.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Logging API [12]\r\n// PSR-3: Logger Interface standard [17]\r\npublic function __construct(\r\n    private readonly LoggerInterface $logger,\r\n) {\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>...</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Logging API [12]\r\n// PSR-3: Logger Interface standard [17]\r\n$this-&gt;logger-&gt;warning(\'Detail view called without parameter\');\r\n$this-&gt;redirectToUri($uri);</pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 1, 'psr-3-logger-interface-standard', 0, '<p>Knowledge about the PSR-3 logging standard for PHP.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>I know about the interfaces defined by PSR-3.</li> 	<li>I know about the standard implementations of PSR-3.</li> 	<li>I know the API methods the PSR-3 LoggerInterface provides for writing log messages.</li> 	<li>I can use PSR-3-based logging in my own extensions.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (18, 12, 1707703429, 1707703208, 0, 0, 0, 0, 256, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Backend plugin preview with record list [A]', '<p>To display a list of data records in the plugin preview in the TYPO3 backend, use the following procedure.</p>\r\n<h2>Implementation</h2>\r\n<ol> 	<li>Complete file Classes/Preview/MyPreviewRenderer.php</li> 	<li>Complete file Resources/Private/Templates/Tccd/BackendPreview/List.html</li> 	<li>Parts in Configuration/TCA/Overrides/tt_content.php</li> </ol>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Backend plugin preview with record list [A]\r\n$GLOBALS[\'TCA\'][\'tt_content\'][\'types\'][\'list\'][\'previewRenderer\'][\'tccdexamples_tccdpluginlist\']\r\n    = Machwert\\TccdExamples\\Preview\\MyPreviewRenderer::class;</pre>', 1, 'backend-plugin-preview-with-record-list-a', 1, '', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (19, 12, 1707826906, 1707826809, 0, 0, 0, 0, 512, 1, 18, '{\"starttime\":\"parent\",\"endtime\":\"parent\"}', , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Backend-Plugin-Vorschau mit Datensatzliste [A]', '<p>Um eine Liste der Datens√§tze in der Plugin-Vorschau im TYPO3-Backend anzuzeigen, gehen Sie wie folgt vor.</p>\r\n<h2>Implementierung</h2>\r\n<ol> 	<li>Vollst√§ndige Datei Classes/Preview/MyPreviewRenderer.php</li> 	<li>Vollst√§ndige Datei Resources/Private/Templates/Tccd/BackendPreview/List.html</li> 	<li>Teile in Configuration/TCA/Overrides/tt_content.php</li> </ol>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Backend plugin preview with record list [A]\r\n$GLOBALS[\'TCA\'][\'tt_content\'][\'types\'][\'list\'][\'previewRenderer\'][\'tccdexamples_tccdpluginlist\']\r\n    = Machwert\\TccdExamples\\Preview\\MyPreviewRenderer::class;</pre>', 1, 'backend-plugin-preview-with-record-list-a', 1, '', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (20, 11, 1710506348, 1707958067, 0, 0, 0, 0, 33, 1, 16, '{\"starttime\":\"parent\",\"endtime\":\"parent\",\"categories\":\"parent\"}', , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bestehende Funktionalit√§t erweitern [16]', '<h2>Haken (Ziel 1)</h2>\r\n<p>Ein Hook ist eine ‚ÄûUnterbrechung‚Äú an einer bestimmten Stelle im aktuellen Programmablauf, um dann Code aus einer ganz anderen Quelle einzubinden.</p>\r\n<p>Es gibt zwei Arten von Haken. Zum einen die Hooks, mit denen man bestimmte Funktionen um weitere Funktionalit√§t erweitern kann und zum anderen Hooks, mit denen man Inhalte ver√§ndern kann.</p>\r\n<p>Wenn m√∂glich, bevorzugen Sie PSR-14-Veranstaltungen.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Implementierung mittels Hooks</strong></p>\r\n<p>1. Datei ext_localconf.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Extending Existing Functionality [16] - Hooks\r\n$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SC_OPTIONS\'][\'t3lib/class.t3lib_tcemain.php\'][\'processDatamapClass\'][\'tccd_examples\']\r\n    = \\Machwert\\TccdExamples\\Hooks\\MyDataHandlerHooks::class;</pre>\r\n<p>2. Dateiklassen/Hooks/MyDataHandlerHooks.php</p>\r\n<p><strong>Testimplementierung</strong></p>\r\n<p>Wird in ‚ÄûTest Datahandler Hook‚Äú als Titel f√ºr den neuen Lehrplan-Datensatz dieser Erweiterung festgelegt.<br /> Die Beschreibung wird nach dem Speichern automatisch mit ‚ÄûTest Datahandler Hook Description‚Äú gef√ºllt.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>PSR-14-Ereignisse (Ziel 2)</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 1, 'bestehende-funktionalitaet-erweitern-16', 1, '<p>Erweiterung der Kern- und Erweiterungsfunktionalit√§t ohne √Ñnderung des Codes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ziele</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>Ich wei√ü, was Hooks sind und welche zwei verschiedenen Arten von Hook-Implementierungen es gibt.</li> 	<li>Ich kenne PSR-14-Ereignisse und wei√ü, wie sie in TYPO3 implementiert werden.</li> 	<li>Ich wei√ü, was userFuncs im TCA sind und wie ich sie nutzen kann.</li> 	<li>Ich kann Stellen identifizieren, an denen TYPO3 die Erweiterung der integrierten Funktionalit√§t erm√∂glicht.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (26, 11, 1707999466, 1707962316, 0, 0, 0, 0, 65, 1, 15, '{\"starttime\":\"parent\",\"endtime\":\"parent\"}', , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'PSR-7: Anfrage/Antwort [15]', '<p>Das PSR-7-basierte Anforderungsobjekt ist in den meisten Kontexten verf√ºgbar. In einigen Szenarios, etwa bei PSR-15-Middlewares oder Backend-Modul-Controllern, wird das PSR-7-Basisanforderungsobjekt als Argument an die aufgerufene Methode √ºbergeben.</p>\r\n<p>In einem <strong>Extbase-Controller</strong> ist das mit dem PSR-7 \\Psr\\Http\\Message\\ServerRequestInterface kompatible Anforderungsobjekt √ºber die Klasseneigenschaft $this-&gt;request verf√ºgbar.</p>\r\n<p>In einem <strong>ViewHelper</strong> k√∂nnen Sie die Rendering-Anfrage aus dem Rendering-Kontext abrufen.</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\n\r\ndeclare(strict_types=1);\r\n\r\nnamespace MyVendor\\MyExtension\\ViewHelpers;\r\n\r\nuse TYPO3\\CMS\\Fluid\\Core\\Rendering\\RenderingContext;\r\nuse TYPO3Fluid\\Fluid\\Core\\Rendering\\RenderingContextInterface;\r\nuse TYPO3Fluid\\Fluid\\Core\\ViewHelper\\AbstractViewHelper;\r\n\r\nfinal class MyViewHelper extends AbstractViewHelper\r\n{\r\n    public static function renderStatic(array $arguments, \\Closure $renderChildrenClosure, RenderingContextInterface $renderingContext): string\r\n    {\r\n        /** @var RenderingContext $renderingContext */\r\n        $request = $renderingContext-&gt;getRequest();\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>In einer <strong>TypoScript-Benutzerfunktion</strong> steht das Request-Objekt als dritter Parameter der aufgerufenen Klassenmethode zur Verf√ºgung.</p>\r\n<p>Als erstes Argument f√ºr die Methode ‚Äûprocess()‚Äú erh√§lt ein <strong>Datenverarbeiter</strong> eine Referenz auf den \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Frontend\\ContentObject\\ContentObjectRenderer. Dieses Objekt stellt eine getRequest()-Methode bereit.</p>\r\n<p>TYPO3 stellt das Request-Objekt auch in der globalen Variablen <strong>$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_REQUEST\']</strong> bereit. Wenn m√∂glich, verwenden Sie es nicht.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Attribute</h3>\r\n<p>Attribute reichern die Anfrage mit weiteren Informationen an. TYPO3 stellt Attribute bereit, die in benutzerdefinierten Implementierungen verwendet werden k√∂nnen.</p>\r\n<p>Die Attribute k√∂nnen √ºber abgerufen werden</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Get all available attributes\r\n$allAttributes = $request-&gt;getAttributes();\r\n\r\n// Get only a specific attribute, here the site entity in frontend context\r\n$site = $request-&gt;getAttribute(\'site\');\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>Die folgenden Attribute sind im Frontend-Kontext verf√ºgbar:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>Anwendungstyp</li> 	<li>Frontend-Controller</li> 	<li>Frontend-Benutzer</li> 	<li>Sprache</li> 	<li>Normalisierte Parameter</li> 	<li>Routenf√ºhrung</li> 	<li>Website</li> </ul>\r\n<p>Die folgenden Attribute sind im Backend-Kontext verf√ºgbar:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>Anwendungstyp</li> 	<li>Normalisierte Parameter</li> 	<li>Route</li> 	<li>Website</li> 	<li>Ziel</li> </ul>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/RequestLifeCycle/Typo3Request.html?highlight=psr%207\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/RequestLifeCycle/Typo3Request.html?highlight=psr%207</a></p>', 1, 'psr-7-anfrage/antwort-15', 1, '<p>Diese Fertigkeit deckt den PSR-Standard f√ºr HTTP-Anfrage-/Antwortobjekte ab.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ziele</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>Ich habe Grundkenntnisse √ºber den Standard PSR-7.</li> 	<li>Ich wei√ü, wie man in PHP mit Anfrage- und Antwortobjekten umgeht.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', '');
INSERT INTO `tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd` (`uid`, `pid`, `tstamp`, `crdate`, `deleted`, `hidden`, `starttime`, `endtime`, `sorting`, `sys_language_uid`, `l10n_parent`, `l10n_state`, `l10n_diffsource`, `t3ver_oid`, `t3ver_wsid`, `t3ver_state`, `t3ver_stage`, `title`, `description`, `version`, `slug`, `categories`, `syllabusdescription`, `link`, `edited`, `images`, `makenewtranslation`, `related_tccds`, `links`) VALUES
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (27, 11, 1707999486, 1707966375, 0, 0, 0, 0, 129, 1, 14, '{\"starttime\":\"parent\",\"endtime\":\"parent\"}', , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kenntnisse √ºber Umgebungsfehlerprotokolle [14]', '<h2>TYPO3 Logfiles</h2>\r\n<p>Die TYPO3-Protokollkonfiguration wird in <strong>$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'LOG\']</strong> festgelegt und normalerweise in typo3conf/LocalConfiguration.php oder typo3conf/AdditionalConfiguration.php.</p>\r\n<p>Das Standardverzeichnis der TYPO3-Fehlerprotokolldatei ist <strong>typo3temp/var/log/.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Auf TYPO3 Logifle kann im TYPO3 Backend unter <strong>System / Log</strong> zugegriffen werden<br /> Auf die TYPO3-Veraltungsprotokolldatei kann nur direkt im Dateisystem zugegriffen werden</p>\r\n<p>Codes f√ºr das Logging Framework sind</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>0 Notfall</li> 	<li>1 Warnung</li> 	<li>2 Kritisch</li> 	<li>3 Fehler</li> 	<li>4 Warnung</li> 	<li>5 Hinweis</li> 	<li>6 Information</li> 	<li>7 Debuggen</li> </ul>\r\n<h2><br /> Webserver (Apache oder Nginx) und PHP-Logdateien</h2>\r\n<p>F√ºr MAMP-Installationen werden Protokolldateien in <strong>MAMP/logs</strong> gespeichert</p>\r\n<p>Hier finden Sie</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>php_error.log</li> 	<li>apache_error.log (oder nginx_error.log)</li> 	<li>mysql_error.log</li> </ul>\r\n<p>Bei Linux-Distributionen befinden sie sich meist in <strong>var/log</strong></p>\r\n\r\n', 1, 'kenntnisse-ueber-umgebungsfehlerprotokolle-14', 2, '<p>M√∂glichkeit, von Systemkomponenten bereitgestellte Protokolle zu finden.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ziele</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>Ich wei√ü, wo sich die Fehlerprotokolle von TYPO3, einem Webserver und PHP befinden.</li> 	<li>Ich kann auf diese Protokolle zugreifen, um in meiner Umgebung auftretende Fehler nachzuverfolgen.</li> 	<li>Ich wei√ü, wie ich Fehlerprotokollmeldungen interpretiere, um den Fehler zu beheben.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (28, 11, 1707999375, 1707966456, 0, 0, 0, 0, 257, 1, 13, '{\"starttime\":\"parent\",\"endtime\":\"parent\"}', , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Debuggen in PHP [13]', '<h2>Ziel 2</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.machwert.de/tipps-und-tricks/tipp/xdebug-phpstorm-und-typo3/\">https://www.machwert.de/tipps-und-tricks/tipp/xdebug-phpstorm-und-typo3/</a></p>', 1, 'debuggen-in-php-13', 2, '<p>Grundkenntnisse √ºber Fehlerverfolgungsmethoden in PHP.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ziele</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>Ich kenne einfache Methoden zum Drucken von Werten zur Ausgabe (var_dump, print_r, echo, die).</li> 	<li>Ich wei√ü, wie man ein Debugging-Tool wie Xdebug einrichtet und verwendet.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (29, 11, 1707990368, 1707990368, 0, 0, 0, 0, 513, 1, 12, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Protokollierungs-API [12]', '<p>Die Protokollierungs-API folgt <strong>PSR-3.</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Alle Protokollschreiber k√∂nnen in Ihren eigenen Klassen verwendet werden. Wenn der Dienst f√ºr die Verwendung von Autowiring konfiguriert ist (in Configuration/Services.yaml), k√∂nnen Sie seit TYPO3 v11 LTS wie folgt einen Logger in die __construct()-Methode Ihrer Klasse (MyVendor\\MyExtension\\MyFolder\\MyClass) einf√ºgen:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\ndeclare(strict_types=1);\r\n\r\nnamespace MyVendor\\MyExtension;\r\n\r\nuse Psr\\Log\\LoggerInterface;\r\n\r\nclass MyClass\r\n{\r\n    public function __construct(\r\n        private readonly LoggerInterface $logger,\r\n    ) {\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>Ausgaben in die Protokolldatei werden wie folgt generiert:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n$this-&gt;logger-&gt;error(\'Passing {value} was unwise.\', [    \r\n    \'value\' =&gt; $value,\r\n    \'other_data\' =&gt; $foo,\r\n]);</pre>\r\n<p>$this-&gt;logger-&gt;warning oder Critical ist ebenfalls m√∂glich</p>\r\n<p>Alternativ kann logger-&gt;log auch mit LogLevel aufgerufen werden:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n$this-&gt;logger-&gt;log(LogLevel::CRITICAL, \'This is an utter failure!\');</pre>\r\n<p>Codes f√ºr das Logging Framework sind</p>\r\n<ul><li><p>0 Notfall</p></li><li><p> 1 Warnung</p></li><li><p> 2 Kritisch</p></li><li><p> 3 Fehler</p></li><li><p> 4 Warnung</p></li><li><p> 5 Hinweis</p></li><li><p> 6 Information</p></li><li><p> 7 Debuggen</p></li></ul>\r\n<h2>Implementierung</h2>\r\n<p>Wenn Sie die Detailansicht (/tccd/detail/) dieser Erweiterung ohne Parameter aufrufen, werden Sie zur Listenseite weitergeleitet. Zu Testzwecken wird ‚ÄûDetailansicht ohne Parameter aufgerufen‚Äú ins Protokoll geschrieben, oder vollst√§ndig:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\nThu, 08 Feb 2024 10:11:26 +0100 [WARNING] request=\"26e20ee8d9732\" component=\"Machwert.TccdExamples.Controller.TccdController\": Detail view called without parameter </pre>', 1, 'protokollierungs-api-12', 2, '<p>Kenntnisse √ºber die von TYPO3 bereitgestellte Protokollierungs-API.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ziele</strong></p>\r\n<ol><li>Ich wei√ü, wie man eine richtige Protokollnachricht verfasst und aus welchen Teilen sie besteht.</li><li> Ich kenne die verschiedenen Protokollebenen und ihre Bedeutung.</li><li> Ich wei√ü, wie ich einen Logger in meinem Code bekomme und verwende.</li><li> Ich kenne mich mit Protokollkan√§len aus und wei√ü, wie ich sie in meinem Code verwende.</li></ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (30, 11, 1707995787, 1707995787, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1794, 1, 11, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fehler in Protokollen nachverfolgen [11]', '<h2>Protokolldateien (Ziel 1)</h2>\r\n<ol><li>PHP ‚Äì Protokolldatei</li><li> Apache- (oder Nginx-)Protokolldatei</li><li> MySQL-Protokolldatei</li><li> TYPO3-Logdatei (Standard: typo3temp/var/log/)</li><li> TYPO3-Abwertungsprotokolldatei (Standard: typo3temp/var/log/)</li></ol>\r\n<p>F√ºr MAMP 1-3 werden in MAMP/logs/ gespeichert.</p>\r\n<h2>Datenbank-Logtabelle (Ziel 1)</h2>\r\n<ul><li>sys_log (TYPO3 Backend / System / Log)</li></ul>\r\n<h2>Adminpanel (Ziel 1)</h2>\r\n<h2>ErrorHandler</h2>\r\n<p>Der ErrorHandler (\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Error\\ErrorHandler) hat folgende Funktionen</p>\r\n<ul><li>Zeigt Fehlermeldungen als Flash-Meldungen im Backend an (wenn ExceptionHandler auf \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Error\\DebugExceptionHandler gesetzt ist)</li><li> Zeigt Fehler als TsLog-Meldungen im Admin-Panel an.</li><li> Protokolliert Fehlermeldungen √ºber die Protokollierungs-API.</li><li> Protokolliert Fehlermeldungen in der Tabelle sys_log. Protokollierte Fehler werden in der Belog-Erweiterung angezeigt (Verwaltungstools &gt; Protokoll).</li></ul>\r\n<h2>TYPO3-Protokollierung</h2>\r\n<p>Codes f√ºr das Protokollierungsframework sind</p>\r\n<ul><li>0 Notfall</li><li> 1 Warnung</li><li> 2 Kritisch</li><li> 3 Fehler</li><li> 4 Warnung</li><li> 5 Hinweis</li><li> 6 Information</li><li> 7 Debuggen</li></ul>\r\n<h2>Konfiguration (Ziel 2)</h2>\r\n<p>In LocalConfiguration.php sind viele Debug-Einstellungen m√∂glich:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\nreturn [\r\n   \'BE\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'debug\' =&gt; true,\r\n   ],\r\n   \'FE\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'debug\' =&gt; true,\r\n   ],\r\n   \'SYS\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'devIPmask\' =&gt; \'*\', // Goal 3\r\n      \'displayErrors\' =&gt; 1,\r\n      \'exceptionalErrors\' =&gt; 28674,\r\n   ],\r\n];\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>Tabelle: SYS-Konfiguration</p>\r\n<table><thead><tr><th><p>Schl√ºssel</p></th><th><p> Datentyp</p></th><th><p> Beschreibung</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><p> Anzeigefehler</p></td><td><p> ganze Zahl</p></td><td><p> Konfiguriert, ob PHP-Fehler angezeigt werden sollen.</p><ul><li><p> 0 = Keine PHP-Fehlermeldungen anzeigen. √úberschreibt den Wert von ‚ÄûExceptionalErrors‚Äú und setzt ihn auf 0 (= keine Fehler werden in Ausnahmen umgewandelt), der konfigurierte ProductionExceptionHandler wird als Ausnahmehandler verwendet</p></li><li><p> 1 = Fehlermeldungen mit dem registrierten Fehlerhandler anzeigen, der konfigurierte debugExceptionHandler wird als Ausnahmehandler verwendet</p></li><li><p> -1 = Standardeinstellung. Mit dieser Option k√∂nnen Sie die PHP-Einstellung display_errors √ºberschreiben. Wenn devIPmask mit der IP-Adresse des Benutzers √ºbereinstimmt, wird der konfigurierte debugExceptionHandler f√ºr Ausnahmen verwendet, andernfalls wird ProductionExceptionHandler verwendet.</p></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><p> errorHandler</p></td><td><p> Zeichenfolge</p></td><td><p> Klassenname zur Behandlung von PHP-Fehlern. Leer lassen, um die Fehlerbehandlung zu deaktivieren.</p><p> Standard: \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Error\\ErrorHandler. Diese Klasse registriert sich selbst als Fehlerbehandler. Es ist in der Lage, Fehlermeldungen an alle verf√ºgbaren Protokollierungssysteme in TYPO3 zu schreiben. Weitere Informationen finden Sie unter <a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/Logging/Index.html#logging\">Logging Framework</a> .</p><p> Zus√§tzlich k√∂nnen die Fehler als Flash-Meldungen im Backend oder im Adminpanel im Frontend angezeigt werden. Die Flash-Meldungen im Backend werden nur angezeigt, wenn sich die Fehler- und Ausnahmebehandlung im ‚ÄûDebug-Modus‚Äú befindet, was der Fall ist, wenn der konfigurierte ‚ÄûdebugExceptionHandler‚Äú als Ausnahmehandler registriert ist (siehe:$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS &#39;][&#39;displayErrors&#39;]).</p><p> Fehler, die als ‚ÄûExceptionalErrors‚Äú registriert sind, werden in Ausnahmen umgewandelt (die vom konfigurierten Ausnahmehandler behandelt werden).</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> errorHandlerErrors</p></td><td><p> ganze Zahl</p></td><td><p> Die E_*-Konstante, die vom Fehlerhandler verarbeitet wird</p><p> Standard: E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> au√üergew√∂hnlichErrors</p></td><td><p> ganze Zahl</p></td><td><p> Die E_*-Konstante, die vom Fehlerhandler als Ausnahme behandelt wird.</p><p> Standard: E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE ^ E_WARNING ^ E_USER_ERROR ^E_USER_NOTICE ^ E_USER_WARNING (4341) und ‚Äû0‚Äú, wenn $GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;displayErrors&#39;] = 0.</p><p> Weitere Einzelheiten zu diesem Wert finden Sie in der PHP-Dokumentation.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> ProductionExceptionHandler</p></td><td><p> Zeichenfolge</p></td><td><p> Klassenname zur Behandlung von Ausnahmen, die im TYPO3-Code auftreten k√∂nnen.</p><p> Lassen Sie das Feld leer, um die Ausnahmebehandlung zu deaktivieren.</p><p> Standard: \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Error\\ProductionExceptionHandler. Dieser Ausnahmehandler zeigt eine nette Fehlermeldung an, wenn etwas schief gelaufen ist. Die Fehlermeldung wird in den konfigurierten Protokollen protokolliert.</p><p> Notiz</p><p> Der konfigurierte ProductionExceptionHandler wird verwendet, wenn $GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;displayErrors&#39;] auf &quot;0&quot; oder auf &quot;-1&quot; gesetzt ist und $GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39; devIPmask&#39;] stimmt nicht √ºberein.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> debugExceptionHandler</p></td><td><p> Zeichenfolge</p></td><td><p> Klassenname zur Behandlung von Ausnahmen, die im TYPO3-Code auftreten k√∂nnen.</p><p> Lassen Sie das Feld leer, um die Ausnahmebehandlung zu deaktivieren.</p><p> Standard: \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Error\\DebugExceptionHandler. Dieser Ausnahmehandler zeigt den vollst√§ndigen Stack-Trace aller aufgetretenen Ausnahmen an. Die Fehlermeldung und der Stacktrace werden in den konfigurierten Protokollen protokolliert.</p><p> Notiz</p><p> Der konfigurierte debugExceptionHandler wird verwendet, wenn $GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;displayErrors&#39;] auf &quot;1&quot; gesetzt ist oder wenn $GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;displayErrors&#39;] &quot; -1‚Äú oder ‚Äû2‚Äú und die $GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;devIPmask&#39;]-√úbereinstimmungen.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> belogErrorReporting</p></td><td><p> ganze Zahl</p></td><td><p> Konfiguriert, welche PHP-Fehler in der Tabelle ‚Äûsys_log‚Äú (Erweiterung: belog) protokolliert werden sollen. Bei der Einstellung ‚Äû0‚Äú werden keine PHP-Fehler in der Tabelle ‚Äûsys_log‚Äú protokolliert.</p><p> Standard: E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE (6135).</p></td></tr></tbody></table>\r\n<p>Tabelle: displayErrors</p>\r\n<table><thead><tr><th><p>Anzeigefehler</p></th><th><p> errorHandlerErrors</p></th><th><p> au√üergew√∂hnlichErrors</p></th><th><p> errorHandler</p></th><th><p> devIPmask</p></th><th><p> Ausnahmehandler</p></th><th><p> display_errors</p><p> (php_ini)</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"><p> -1</p></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><p> E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE</p></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><p> E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE ^ E_WARNING ^ E_USER_ERROR ^ E_USER_NOTICE</p></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><p> TYPO3CMS CoreError ErrorHandler</p></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><p> Angelegenheiten</p></td><td><p> Wenn devIPmask √ºbereinstimmt: debugExceptionHandler</p></td><td><p> Nicht ge√§ndert</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> Wenn devIPmask nicht √ºbereinstimmt: ProductionExceptionHandler</p></td><td><p> Nicht ge√§ndert</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> 0</p></td><td><p> E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE</p></td><td><p> <strong>0</strong> <strong>(keine Fehler werden in Ausnahmen umgewandelt)</strong></p></td><td><p> TYPO3CMS CoreError ErrorHandler</p></td><td><p> Spielt keine Rolle</p></td><td><p> Produktion ExceptionHandler</p></td><td><p> <strong>0 (Aus)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> 1</p></td><td><p> E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE</p></td><td><p> E_ALL ^ E_NOTICE ^ E_WARNING ^ E_USER_ERROR ^ E_USER_NOTICE ^ E_USER_WARNING</p></td><td><p> TYPO3CMS CoreError ErrorHandler</p></td><td><p> Spielt keine Rolle</p></td><td><p> debugException-Handler</p></td><td><p> <strong>1 (Ein)</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table>\r\n<p>Siehe TYPO3 v10-Dokumentation (aber gr√∂√ütenteils g√ºltig f√ºr TYPO3 v11):<br /> <a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/ErrorAndExceptionHandling/Configuration/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/ErrorAndExceptionHandling/Configuration/Index.html</a></p>\r\n\r\n', 1, 'fehler-in-protokollen-nachverfolgen-11', 3, '<p>Kenntnisse √ºber Protokollquellen und deren Nutzung zur Behebung von Fehlern.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ziele</strong></p>\r\n<ol><li>Ich wei√ü, wo ich suchen muss, wenn meine Instanz Fehlermeldungen oder wei√üe Seiten ausgibt.</li><li> Ich wei√ü, welche Konfigurationsoptionen die Fehlerausgabe von TYPO3 und Extbase definieren.</li><li> Ich wei√ü, wie man die Fehlerausgabe auf Entwicklungsmaschinen oder bestimmte IPs auf Live-Instanzen beschr√§nkt.</li></ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (31, 11, 1707995804, 1707995804, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1922, 1, 10, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'TYPO3-Debugging-Dienstprogramme [10]', '<h2>Aufbau</h2>\r\n<p>In LocalConfiguration.php sind viele Debug-Einstellungen m√∂glich:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;?php\r\nreturn [\r\n   \'BE\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'debug\' =&gt; true,\r\n   ],\r\n   \'FE\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'debug\' =&gt; true,\r\n   ],\r\n   \'SYS\' =&gt; [\r\n      \'devIPmask\' =&gt; \'*\',\r\n      \'displayErrors\' =&gt; 1,\r\n      \'exceptionalErrors\' =&gt; 28674,\r\n   ],\r\n];\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>Folgende Konfigurationswerte sind von Interesse:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/BE.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-BE-debug\">$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;BE&#39;][&#39;debug&#39;]</a></p>\r\n<p>Wenn diese Option aktiviert ist, ist die Anmeldeaktualisierung deaktiviert und pageRenderer wird auf den Debug-Modus eingestellt. Au√üerdem wird der Feldname an die Feldbeschriftung angeh√§ngt.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/FE.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-FE-debug\">$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;FE&#39;][&#39;debug&#39;]</a></p>\r\n<p>Wenn aktiviert, wird die gesamte Parse-Zeit der Seite als HTTP-Antwortheader X-TYPO3-Parsetime hinzugef√ºgt.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-devIPmask\">$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;devIPmask&#39;]</a></p>\r\n<p>Definiert eine Liste von IP-Adressen, die die Anzeige der Entwicklungsausgabe erm√∂glichen. Durch die Einstellung ‚Äû*‚Äú werden alle zugelassen. Wenn Sie es auf eine leere Zeichenfolge setzen, ist keine zul√§ssig.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-displayErrors\">$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;displayErrors&#39;]</a></p>\r\n<p>Konfiguriert, ob PHP-Fehler oder Ausnahmen angezeigt werden sollen.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-errorHandler\">$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;errorHandler&#39;]</a></p>\r\n<p>Klassenname zur Behandlung von PHP-Fehlern. Leer lassen, um die Fehlerbehandlung zu deaktivieren.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-errorHandlerErrors\">$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;errorHandlerErrors&#39;]</a></p>\r\n<p>Die E_*-Konstanten, die vom Fehlerhandler verarbeitet werden.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-exceptionalErrors\">$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;ExceptionalErrors&#39;]</a></p>\r\n<p>Die E_*-Konstante, die vom Standard-errorHandler in eine Ausnahme umgewandelt wird.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-productionExceptionHandler\">$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;produktionExceptionHandler&#39;]</a></p>\r\n<p>Der Standard-Ausnahmebehandler zeigt eine nette Fehlermeldung an, wenn etwas schief geht. Die Fehlermeldung wird in den konfigurierten Protokollen protokolliert.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-debugExceptionHandler\">$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;debugExceptionHandler&#39;]</a></p>\r\n<p>Der standardm√§√üige Debug-Ausnahmehandler zeigt den vollst√§ndigen Stack-Trace aller aufgetretenen Ausnahmen an. Die Fehlermeldung und der Stacktrace werden in den konfigurierten Protokollen protokolliert.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/Configuration/Typo3ConfVars/SYS.html#confval-GLOBALS-TYPO3_CONF_VARS-SYS-belogErrorReporting\">$GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;SYS&#39;][&#39;belogErrorReporting&#39;]</a></p>\r\n<p>Konfiguriert, welche PHP-Fehler in der sys_log-Tabelle protokolliert werden sollen.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Frontend-Debug</h2>\r\n<ul><li>Im PHP-Code: print_r, echo, var_dump(), debug(), DebugUtility::debug</li></ul>\r\n<pre>\r\n\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Utility\\DebugUtility::debug($filterParameter, \'filterParameter\');</pre>\r\n<ul><li>Im Frontend: AdminPanel</li><li> In TypoScript oder EXT:some_extension/Configuration/TypoScript/setup.typoscript</li></ul>\r\n<pre>\r\nconfig.contentObjectExceptionHandler = 0\r\n</pre>\r\n<h2>Backend-Debug</h2>\r\n<p>Um zus√§tzliche Debug-Informationen im Backend anzuzeigen, setzen Sie $GLOBALS[&#39;TYPO3_CONF_VARS&#39;][&#39;BE&#39;][&#39;debug&#39;] in LocalConfiguration.php und melden Sie sich mit einem Administratorkonto an.</p>\r\n<h2>SQL-Debug</h2>\r\n<p>Es kann sehr hilfreich sein, die endg√ºltigen Anweisungen von queryBuilder mit debug($queryBuilder-&gt;getSQL()) zu debuggen.</p>\r\n<h2>Gut zu wissen</h2>\r\n<p>Im Debugmodus komprimiert oder verkettet der Seitenrenderer keine JavaScript- oder CSS-Ressourcen.</p>\r\n<h2>Links</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/ErrorAndExceptionHandling/Configuration/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/ErrorAndExceptionHandling/Configuration/Index.html</a><br /> <a href=\"https://www.php.net/manual/en/errorfunc.constants.php\">https://www.php.net/manual/en/errorfunc.constants.php</a></p>', 1, 'typo3-debugging-dienstprogramme-10', 2, '<p>Kenntnisse √ºber die von TYPO3 bereitgestellten Debugging-Dienstprogramme.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ziele</strong></p>\r\n<ul><li>Ich kenne die eingebaute Mechanik zur Ausgabe von Debug-Meldungen:<ul><li> Extbase DebuggerUtility</li><li> DebugUtility</li><li> Administrationsmen√º</li></ul></li><li> Ich wei√ü, wie man Debug-Ausgaben zum Frontend hinzuf√ºgt.</li><li> Ich wei√ü, wie man Debug-Ausgaben zum Backend hinzuf√ºgt.</li></ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (32, 11, 1708517126, 1708517126, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2051, 1, 9, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Verwendung von Abfragebeschr√§nkungen [9]', '<h2>Implementierung</h2>\r\n<h3>In der Datei Classes/Domain/Repository/TccdRepository.php</h3>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Using Query Restrictions [9]\r\nif ((isset($filterParameter[\'showHidden\']) &amp;&amp; $filterParameter[\'showHidden\']) OR\r\n    (isset($filterParameter[\'showDeleted\']) &amp;&amp; $filterParameter[\'showDeleted\'])) {\r\n    $query-&gt;getQuerySettings()-&gt;setIgnoreEnableFields(true);\r\n}\r\nif (isset($filterParameter[\'showDeleted\']) &amp;&amp; $filterParameter[\'showDeleted\']) {\r\n    $query-&gt;getQuerySettings()-&gt;setIncludeDeleted(true);\r\n}\r\nif (isset($filterParameter[\'ignoreStorage\']) &amp;&amp; $filterParameter[\'ignoreStorage\']) {\r\n    $query-&gt;getQuerySettings()-&gt;setRespectStoragePage(false);\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Standardeinschr√§nkungen in Repositorys</h2>\r\n<ul><li>sys_lingual_uid IN (0,-1)</li><li> pid = 0</li><li> t3ver_oid =0</li><li> versteckt = 0</li><li> gel√∂scht = 0</li><li> Startzeit &lt;= jetzt</li><li> endtime = 0 ODER &gt; jetzt</li></ul>\r\n<h2>Andere m√∂gliche Implementierungen</h2>\r\n<p>Nicht im Repository, sondern z. B. im Controller mit $queryBuilder:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\ConnectionPool;</em>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\Query\\Restriction\\StartTimeRestriction</em>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\Query\\Restriction\\EndTimeRestriction</em>\r\n<em>// Remove starttime and endtime, but keep hidden and deleted</em>\r\n\r\n$queryBuilder = $this-&gt;connectionPool-&gt;getQueryBuilderForTable(\'tt_content\');\r\n$queryBuilder\r\n    -&gt;getRestrictions()\r\n    -&gt;removeByType(StartTimeRestriction::class)\r\n    -&gt;removeByType(EndTimeRestriction::class);</pre>\r\n<p>Oder entfernen Sie alle Einschr√§nkungen und f√ºgen Sie dann die ‚Äûgel√∂schte‚Äú Einschr√§nkung hinzu:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Utility\\GeneralUtility;\r\n// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\Connection;</em>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\ConnectionPool;</em>\r\n<em>// use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Database\\Query\\Restriction\\DeletedRestriction\r\n</em>\r\n<em>// Remove all restrictions but add DeletedRestriction again</em>\r\n<em>// Result SQL: SELECT `uid`, `bodytext` FROM `tt_content` WHERE (`pid` = 42) AND (`tt_content`.`deleted` = 0)</em>\r\n\r\n$queryBuilder = $this-&gt;connectionPool-&gt;getQueryBuilderForTable(\'tt_content\');\r\n\r\n$queryBuilder\r\n    -&gt;getRestrictions()\r\n    -&gt;removeAll()\r\n    -&gt;add(GeneralUtility::makeInstance(DeletedRestriction::class));\r\n\r\n$result = $queryBuilder\r\n    -&gt;select(\'uid\', \'bodytext\')\r\n    -&gt;from(\'tt_content\')\r\n    -&gt;where($queryBuilder-&gt;expr()-&gt;eq(\r\n        \'pid\',\r\n        $queryBuilder-&gt;createNamedParameter($pid, Connection::PARAM_INT)\r\n    ))\r\n    -&gt;executeQuery()\r\n    -&gt;fetchAllAssociative(();</pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Erl√§uterung</h2>\r\n<p>Die Methode ‚ÄûremoveByType()‚Äú des RestrictionBuilder kann auch verwendet werden, um ausgeblendete Datens√§tze abzurufen, wenn der Query Builder (Doctrine DBAL) verwendet wird. ‚ÄûTypen‚Äú sind:</p>\r\n<ul><li>HiddenRestriction</li><li> Gel√∂schteEinschr√§nkung</li><li> StartTimeRestriction</li><li> EndTimeRestriction</li><li> FrontendGroupRestriction</li></ul>\r\n<p>Und kann wie folgt entfernt werden:</p>\r\n<ul><li>$queryBuilder-&gt;getRestrictions()-&gt;removeByType(HiddenRestriction::class);</li></ul>\r\n<p>In Extbase-Repositorys k√∂nnen die Abfrageeinstellungen setIgnoreEnableFields() und setEnableFieldsToBeIgnored() entsprechend verwendet werden, um ausgeblendete oder gel√∂schte Elemente abzurufen.</p>\r\n<ul><li>$querySettings-&gt;setIgnoreEnableFields(true);</li><li> $querySettings-&gt;setEnableFieldsToBeIgnored([&#39;deleted&#39;, &#39;disabled&#39;]);</li></ul>\r\n<p>Um auch gel√∂schte Elemente (aber keine versteckten) zu erhalten, kann auch die folgende Methode verwendet werden:</p>\r\n<ul><li>$querySettings-&gt;setIncludeDeleted(true);</li></ul>\r\n<p>setIncludeHidden() existiert nicht.</p>', 1, 'verwendung-von-abfragebeschraenkungen-9', 2, '<p>So beschr√§nken Sie Datenbankabfragen.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ziele</strong></p>\r\n<ul><li>Ich kenne die in TYPO3 automatisch angewendeten Restriktionscontainer.</li><li> Ich kenne die verf√ºgbaren Einschr√§nkungen und deren Verwendung.</li><li> Ich wei√ü, wie ich die angewendeten Einschr√§nkungen √§ndern kann.</li></ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (33, 11, 1708517130, 1708517130, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2054, 1, 8, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Verwendung des QueryBuilder [8]', '<p>In TYPO3 k√∂nnen Datenbankabfragen im MVC-Modell √ºber das Repository oder manuell √ºber den Query Builder implementiert werden. Der Abfrage-Builder ist n√ºtzlich, wenn Sie Datenbankabfragen f√ºr Tabellen erstellen m√∂chten, die kein Modell haben, oder wenn komplexere Datenbankabfragen notwendig sind. INNER- und LEFT-JOINS k√∂nnen auch mit dem Abfrage-Builder implementiert werden.</p>\r\n<h2>Hinweise</h2>\r\n<ul><li>Abfragen in der Abfragesprache von Extbase werden automatisch maskiert. In TYPO3-Repositories ist $this vom Typ TYPO3\\CMS\\Extbase\\Persistence\\QueryInterface.</li><li> Wenn Sie QueryBuilder verwenden: Instanziieren und initialisieren Sie den Abfrage-Builder niemals manuell mithilfe der Abh√§ngigkeitsinjektion oder GeneralUtility::makeInstance(), da Ihnen sonst wichtige Abh√§ngigkeiten und die Laufzeiteinrichtung entgehen.</li><li> Der QueryBuilder speichert den internen Status und darf nicht f√ºr verschiedene Abfragen wiederverwendet werden. Dar√ºber hinaus geht eine Wiederverwendung mit <a href=\"https://www.derhansen.de/2023/10/the-pitfalls-of-reusing-typo3-querybuilder-analyzing-a-performance-bottleneck.html\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">erheblichen Leistungseinbu√üen und Speicherverbrauch</a> einher. <strong>Verwenden Sie einen Abfrage-Generator pro Abfrage.</strong> Erhalten Sie eine neue, indem Sie $connection-&gt;createQueryBuilder() aufrufen, wenn es sich um dieselbe Tabelle handelt, oder verwenden Sie $connectionPool-&gt;getQueryBuilderForTable() f√ºr eine Abfrage an eine andere Tabelle. Keine Sorge, das Erstellen dieser Objektinstanzen geht recht schnell.</li></ul>\r\n<h2>Implementierung</h2>\r\n<h3>In der Datei Classes/Domain/Repository/TccdRepository.php</h3>\r\n<pre>\r\npublic function findAllCategories(): QueryResultInterface|array\r\n{\r\n    // Doctrine DBAL [3]\r\n    // Using the QueryBuilder [8]\r\n    $table = \'sys_category\';\r\n    $queryBuilder = GeneralUtility::makeInstance(ConnectionPool::class)-&gt;getConnectionForTable($table)-&gt;createQueryBuilder();\r\n\r\n    $queryBuilder\r\n        -&gt;select(\'*\')\r\n        -&gt;from($table);\r\n\r\n    $result = $queryBuilder-&gt;executeQuery();\r\n\r\n    while ($row = $result-&gt;fetchAssociative()) {\r\n        $allRows[$row[\'uid\']] = $row;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return $allRows;\r\n}</pre>\r\n<h2>Links</h2>\r\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/QueryBuilder/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/QueryBuilder/Index.htm</a></li><li> <a href=\"https://t3campus.de/typo3-lernen/der-typo3-querybuilder/\">https://t3campus.de/typo3-lernen/der-typo3-querybuilder/</a> (Deutsch)</li></ul>', 1, 'verwendung-des-querybuilder-8', 2, '<p>So schreiben Sie Abfragen in TYPO3.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Ziele</strong></h3>\r\n<ul><li>Ich wei√ü, wie man den in TYPO3 integrierten QueryBuilder verwendet.</li><li> Ich wei√ü, wie man eine sichere Abfrage schreibt, die auf verschiedene DBMS abzielen kann.</li></ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (34, 11, 1708518129, 1708518129, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2057, 1, 7, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Datenbankverwaltungssystem (DBMS) [7]', '<p><strong>TYPO3 setzt auf die Speicherung seiner Daten in einem relationalen Datenbankverwaltungssystem (RDBMS)</strong> . Die Doctrine DBAL-Komponente wird verwendet, um die Verbindung zu verschiedenen Datenbankverwaltungssystemen zu erm√∂glichen. Am h√§ufigsten wird weiterhin MySQL/MariaDB verwendet, aber dank Doctrine sind auch andere wie PostgreSQL und SQLite eine Option.</p>\r\n<h2>Die Verwendung von mehr als einer Datenbank, z. B. f√ºr spezielle Tabellen, ist m√∂glich</h2>\r\n<p>In der Datei typo3conf/LocalConfigurations.php oder typo3conf/Additionalconfiguration.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// [...]\r\n\'DB\' =&gt; [\r\n    \'Connections\' =&gt; [\r\n        \'Default\' =&gt; [\r\n            \'charset\' =&gt; \'utf8\',\r\n            \'dbname\' =&gt; \'default_dbname\',\r\n            \'driver\' =&gt; \'mysqli\',\r\n            \'host\' =&gt; \'default_host\',\r\n            \'password\' =&gt; \'***\',\r\n            \'port\' =&gt; 3306,\r\n            \'user\' =&gt; \'default_user\',\r\n        ],\r\n        \'Syslog\' =&gt; [\r\n            \'charset\' =&gt; \'utf8\',\r\n            \'dbname\' =&gt; \'syslog_dbname\',\r\n            \'driver\' =&gt; \'mysqli\',\r\n            \'host\' =&gt; \'syslog_host\',\r\n            \'password\' =&gt; \'***\',\r\n            \'port\' =&gt; 3306,\r\n            \'user\' =&gt; \'syslog_user\',\r\n        ],\r\n    ],\r\n    \'TableMapping\' =&gt; [\r\n        \'sys_log\' =&gt; \'Syslog\'\r\n    ],\r\n],\r\n// [...]</pre>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>Verkn√ºpfung</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/Introduction/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/Introduction/Index.html</a></p>', 1, 'datenbankverwaltungssystem-dbms-7', 2, '<p>Kenntnisse √ºber DBMS.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Ziele</strong></h3>\r\n<ul><li>Ich wei√ü, was ein DBMS ist und wof√ºr es verwendet wird.</li><li> Ich kann einige Beispiele nennen.</li><li> Ich wei√ü, was der Begriff ‚Äûrelational‚Äú im Kontext von DBMS bedeutet.</li></ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (35, 11, 1708518132, 1708518132, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2065, 1, 6, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Zugriff auf FlexForm-Daten [6]', '<p>Auf FlexForm-Daten kann problemlos im Controller zugegriffen und an die Fluid-Vorlage √ºbergeben werden.</p>\r\n<h2>1. In der Controller-Datei Classes/Controller/TccdController.php</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\n$this-&gt;view-&gt;assign(\'settings\', $this-&gt;settings);</pre>\r\n<h2>2. In der Fluid-Vorlagendatei Resources/Private/Partials/Tccd/ListAndSearch.html</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;f:comment&gt;[6] - Accessing FlexForm Data&lt;/f:comment&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;\r\n    &lt;f:if condition=\"{settings.singlePid}\"&gt;\r\n        &lt;f:then&gt;\r\n            &lt;f:link.action pageUid=\"{settings.singlePid}\" action=\"show\" arguments=\"{tccd : tccd}\"&gt;{tccd.title}&lt;/f:link.action&gt;\r\n        &lt;/f:then&gt;\r\n        &lt;f:else&gt;\r\n            &lt;f:link.action action=\"show\" arguments=\"{tccd : tccd}\"&gt;{tccd.title}&lt;/f:link.action&gt;\r\n        &lt;/f:else&gt;\r\n    &lt;/f:if&gt;\r\n&lt;/td&gt;</pre>', 1, 'zugriff-auf-flexform-daten-6', 2, '<p>Verwendung der in FlexForms bereitgestellten Daten in Plugin-CEs und benutzerdefinierten Datens√§tzen.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Ziele</strong></h3>\r\n<ul><li>Ich wei√ü, wie FlexForm-Daten in der Datenbank gespeichert werden.</li><li> Ich kann Daten aus einem FlexForm-Feld extrahieren.</li><li> Ich kann den Inhalt eines FlexForm-Felds √§ndern.</li></ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (36, 11, 1708518213, 1708518213, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2081, 1, 5, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Flexform-Konfigurationsdatenstruktur [5]', '', 1, 'flexform-konfigurationsdatenstruktur-5', 2, '<p>So erstellen und konfigurieren Sie eine Datenstruktur f√ºr die Konfiguration meines Plugins.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ziele</strong></p>\r\n<ul><li>Ich wei√ü, wie die Konfiguration durch den Inhaltstyp ‚ÄûPlugin‚Äú verwaltet wird.</li><li> Ich kann eine benutzerdefinierte Konfigurationsdatenstruktur f√ºr mein Plugin bereitstellen.</li></ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (37, 11, 1708518221, 1708518221, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2113, 1, 4, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dateiabstraktionsschicht (FAL) [4]', '<p><strong>Der File Abstraction Layer (FAL) ist ein Werkzeugkasten f√ºr den Umgang mit Medien.</strong><br /></p>\r\n<h2>1. TCA in der Datei Configuration/TCA/tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd.php</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\n// [4] - File abstraction layer (FAL)\r\n\'images\' =&gt; [\r\n    \'exclude\' =&gt; true,\r\n    \'label\' =&gt; \'LLL:EXT:tccd_examples/Resources/Private/Language/locallang_db.xlf:tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd.images\',\r\n    \'config\' =&gt; \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Utility\\ExtensionManagementUtility::getFileFieldTCAConfig(\r\n        \'images\',\r\n        [\r\n            \'appearance\' =&gt; [\r\n                \'createNewRelationLinkTitle\' =&gt; \'LLL:EXT:frontend/Resources/Private/Language/locallang_ttc.xlf:images.addFileReference\'\r\n            ],\r\n            \'foreign_types\' =&gt; [\r\n                \'0\' =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ],\r\n                \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\File::FILETYPE_TEXT =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ],\r\n                \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\File::FILETYPE_IMAGE =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ],\r\n                \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\File::FILETYPE_AUDIO =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ],\r\n                \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\File::FILETYPE_VIDEO =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ],\r\n                \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\File::FILETYPE_APPLICATION =&gt; [\r\n                    \'showitem\' =&gt; \'\r\n                    --palette--;LLL:EXT:lang/locallang_tca.xlf:sys_file_reference.imageoverlayPalette;imageoverlayPalette,\r\n                    --palette--;;filePalette\'\r\n                ]\r\n            ],\r\n            \'foreign_match_fields\' =&gt; [\r\n                \'fieldname\' =&gt; \'images\',\r\n                \'tablenames\' =&gt; \'tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd\',\r\n                \'table_local\' =&gt; \'sys_file\',\r\n            ],\r\n            \'maxitems\' =&gt; 1\r\n        ],\r\n        $GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'GFX\'][\'imagefile_ext\']\r\n    ),\r\n],</pre>\r\n<p>...</p>\r\n<h2>2. Modellanpassung in der Datei Classes/Domain/Model/Tccd.php</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\n/**\r\n * @var ObjectStorage&lt;FileReference&gt;\r\n * @Lazy\r\n */\r\nprotected ObjectStorage $images;\r\n\r\npublic function initializeObject(): void\r\n{\r\n    $this-&gt;category = new ObjectStorage();\r\n    $this-&gt;images = new ObjectStorage();\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>...</p>\r\n<pre>\r\npublic function addImages(FileReference $images): void\r\n{\r\n    $this-&gt;images-&gt;attach($images);\r\n}\r\n\r\npublic function removeImages(FileReference $imagesToRemove): void\r\n{\r\n    $this-&gt;images-&gt;detach($imagesToRemove);\r\n}\r\n\r\npublic function getImages(): ?ObjectStorage\r\n{\r\n    return $this-&gt;images;\r\n}\r\n\r\npublic function setImages(?ObjectStorage $images): void\r\n{\r\n    $this-&gt;images = $images;\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<ul> </ul>\r\n<h2>3. Ausgabe in der Datei Resources/Private/Partials/Tccd/Properties.html</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;f:comment&gt;[4] - File abstraction layer (FAL)&lt;/f:comment&gt;\r\n&lt;f:if condition=\"{tccd.images}\"&gt;\r\n    &lt;div class=\"tccd-images\"&gt;\r\n       &lt;f:for each=\"{tccd.images}\" as=\"image\"&gt;\r\n          &lt;div class=\"tccd-image-item\"&gt;\r\n             &lt;f:image src=\"{image.uid}\" alt=\"\" treatIdAsReference=\"TRUE\" width=\"{settings.detail.imageWidth}\" height=\"{settings.detail.imageHeight}\" /&gt;\r\n          &lt;/div&gt;\r\n       &lt;/f:for&gt;\r\n    &lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;/f:if&gt;\r\n\r\n</pre>\r\n<h2>Links</h2>\r\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/Fal/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/Fal/Index.html</a></li></ul>', 1, 'dateiabstraktionsschicht-fal-4', 1, '<p>Informieren Sie sich √ºber die transparente Einbindung externer Dateiquellen in TYPO3.</p>\r\n<h3>Ziele</h3>\r\n<ul><li>Ich wei√ü, dass es eine Abstraktionsschicht zwischen tats√§chlichen Dateispeichern und ihrer Handhabung in TYPO3 gibt.</li></ul>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (38, 11, 1710757492, 1709802049, 0, 0, 0, 0, 24, 1, 17, '{\"starttime\":\"parent\",\"endtime\":\"parent\",\"categories\":\"parent\"}', , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'PSR-3: Logger-Schnittstellenstandard [17]', '', 1, 'psr-3-logger-schnittstellenstandard-17', 0, '<p>Kenntnisse √ºber den PSR-3-Protokollierungsstandard f√ºr PHP.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ziele</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>Ich kenne die von PSR-3 definierten Schnittstellen.</li> 	<li>Ich kenne die Standardimplementierungen von PSR-3.</li> 	<li>Ich kenne die API-Methoden, die das PSR-3 LoggerInterface zum Schreiben von Protokollnachrichten bereitstellt.</li> 	<li>Ich kann die PSR-3-basierte Protokollierung in meinen eigenen Erweiterungen verwenden.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 1, '', '');
INSERT INTO `tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd` (`uid`, `pid`, `tstamp`, `crdate`, `deleted`, `hidden`, `starttime`, `endtime`, `sorting`, `sys_language_uid`, `l10n_parent`, `l10n_state`, `l10n_diffsource`, `t3ver_oid`, `t3ver_wsid`, `t3ver_state`, `t3ver_stage`, `title`, `description`, `version`, `slug`, `categories`, `syllabusdescription`, `link`, `edited`, `images`, `makenewtranslation`, `related_tccds`, `links`) VALUES
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (39, 11, 1710938914, 1709802183, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Caching Framework [18]', '<h3>Goal 1: Use existing caches</h3>\r\n<p>Generally in typo3conf/LocalConfiguration.php&nbsp;or&nbsp;typo3conf/AdditionalConfiguration.php with</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n$GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'caching\'][\'cacheConfigurations\'][\'pages\'][\'backend\'] = \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Cache\\Backend\\FileBackend::class;</pre>\r\n<p>Example for Redis:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n$redisHost = \'127.0.0.1\';\r\n$redisPort = 6379;\r\n$cachesForRedis = [\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; \'pages\' =&gt; 86400*30,\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; \'pagesection\' =&gt; 86400*30,\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; \'hash\' =&gt; 86400*30,\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; \'rootline\' =&gt; 86400*30,\r\n];\r\n$redisDatabaseNumber = 0;\r\nforeach ($cachesForRedis as $cacheName =&gt; $lifetime) {\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; $GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'caching\'][\'cacheConfigurations\'][$cacheName][\'backend\'] = \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Cache\\Backend\\RedisBackend::class;\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; $GLOBALS[\'TYPO3_CONF_VARS\'][\'SYS\'][\'caching\'][\'cacheConfigurations\'][$cacheName][\'options\'] = [\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \'database\' =&gt; $redisDatabaseNumber++,\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \'hostname\' =&gt; $redisHost,\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \'port\' =&gt; $redisPort,\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \'defaultLifetime\' =&gt; $lifetime\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; ];\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>‚ÄûClear Frontend Caches‚Äú button in TYPO3 empties: pages, pagesection, rootline, hash / cache_hash</p>\r\n<h3>Goal 2: Register and use custom caches</h3>\r\n<p>In Configuration/Services.yaml you can register own caches (not implemented):</p>\r\n<p>services:<br /> &nbsp; _defaults:<br /> &nbsp; &nbsp; autowire: true<br /> &nbsp; &nbsp; autoconfigure: true<br /> &nbsp; &nbsp; public: false<br /> <br /> &nbsp; cache.mycache:<br /> &nbsp; &nbsp; class: TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Cache\\Frontend\\FrontendInterface<br /> &nbsp; &nbsp; factory: [\'@TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Cache\\CacheManager\', \'getCache\']<br /> &nbsp; &nbsp; arguments: [\'mycache\']</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://b13.com/blog/caching-in-typo3-part-3\">https://b13.com/blog/caching-in-typo3-part-3</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://usetypo3.com/di-and-events-example/\">https://usetypo3.com/di-and-events-example/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Info</h3>\r\n<p>The following cache groups exist</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>pages<br /> 	Frontend-related caches.</li> 	<li>system<br /> 	System caches. Flushing system caches should be avoided as much as possible, as rebuilding them requires significant resources.</li> 	<li>lowlevel<br /> 	Low-level caches. Flushing low-level caches manually should be avoided completely.</li> 	<li>all<br /> 	All other caches.</li> </ul>\r\n<p>Notes:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>The&nbsp;\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Cache\\CacheManager&nbsp;was used before TYPO3 v10.1 to retrieve an object implementing&nbsp;FrontendInterface. It is now recommended to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/CachingFramework/Developer/Index.html#caching-developer-example\">use dependency injection</a>&nbsp;to retrieve this object and no longer use the&nbsp;CacheManager&nbsp;directly.</li> 	<li>Do not use the&nbsp;CacheManager&nbsp;in&nbsp;ext_localconf.php&nbsp;- instead load caches on demand at the place where they are needed.</li> </ul>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/CachingFramework/Architecture/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/main/en-us/ApiOverview/CachingFramework/Architecture/Index.html</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Cache Tags in own extension (implemented)</h3>\r\n<p>File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Classes/Controller/TccdController.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// The Caching Framework [18]\r\n$this-&gt;addCacheTags(\'RecordName_\' . $tccd-&gt;getUid());</pre>\r\n<pre>\r\n// The Caching Framework [18]\r\npublic function addCacheTags($cacheTag) {\r\n    // do this only in frontend\r\n    if (!empty($GLOBALS[\'TSFE\']) &amp;&amp; is_object($GLOBALS[\'TSFE\'])) {\r\n        // only set the tag once in one request, so cache statically if it has been done\r\n        static $cacheTagsSet = FALSE;\r\n\r\n        /** @var $typoScriptFrontendController \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Frontend\\Controller\\TypoScriptFrontendController  */\r\n        $typoScriptFrontendController = $GLOBALS[\'TSFE\'];\r\n        if (!$cacheTagsSet) {\r\n            $typoScriptFrontendController-&gt;addCacheTags(array($cacheTag));\r\n            $cacheTagsSet = TRUE;\r\n        }\r\n        $this-&gt;typoScriptFrontendController = $typoScriptFrontendController;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>To flush the cache of all detail pages following method (not implemented) could be used:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\npublic function removeCacheTag($cacheTag) {\r\n    $cacheManager = GeneralUtility::makeInstance(CacheManager::class);\r\n    $cacheManager-&gt;flushCachesByTag($cacheTag);\r\n}\r\n</pre>', 1, 'the-caching-framework-18', 0, '<p>This skill covers the Core\'s caching framework. It shows how to use existings caches and register custom caches and the types of cache frontends and backends. Additional topics are expiration and tagging of cache entries and flushing of caches.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<p>I can:</p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>use existing caches</li> 	<li>register and use custom caches</li> 	<li>decide which types of cache frontends and backends to use for which purpose</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', 't3://page?uid=8,t3://page?uid=9,https://www.test.de,t3://page?uid=13'),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (40, 12, 1710198128, 1710197881, 0, 0, 0, 0, 128, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Enable preview from TYPO3 backend for datasets [B]', '<h2>Implementation</h2>\r\n<p>1. File typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Configuration/page.tsconfig</p>\r\n<pre>\r\nTCEMAIN.preview {\r\n    tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd {\r\n        previewPageId = 1\r\n        useDefaultLanguageRecord = 0\r\n        fieldToParameterMap {\r\n            uid = tx_tccdexamples_tccdpluginshow[tccd]\r\n        }\r\n        additionalGetParameters {\r\n            tx_tccdexamples_tccdpluginshow.controller = Tccd\r\n            tx_tccdexamples_tccdpluginshow.action = show\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>2. File typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/ext_localconf.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n# Enable preview from TYPO3 backend for datasets [B]\r\n$versionInformation = GeneralUtility::makeInstance(Typo3Version::class);\r\n// Only include page.tsconfig if TYPO3 version is below 12 so that it is not imported twice.\r\nif ($versionInformation-&gt;getMajorVersion() &lt; 12) {\r\n    ExtensionManagementUtility::addPageTSConfig(\r\n        \'@import \"EXT:tccd_examples/Configuration/page.tsconfig\"\'\r\n    );\r\n}</pre>', 1, 'enable-preview-from-typo3-backend-for-datasets', 0, '', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (41, 12, 1710335546, 1710335236, 0, 0, 0, 0, 64, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Include multi select related dataset form field in TCA [C]', '<p>File typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/ext_tables.sql</p>\r\n<pre>\r\nCREATE TABLE tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd (\r\n...\r\nrelated_tccds varchar(255) NOT NULL DEFAULT \'\',\r\n...\r\n);\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>File typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Configuration/TCA/tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n# Include multi select related dataset form field in TCA [C]\r\n\'related_tccds\' =&gt; [\r\n    \'label\' =&gt; \'LLL:EXT:tccd_examples/Resources/Private/Language/locallang_db.xlf:tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd.related_tccds\',\r\n    \'config\' =&gt; [\r\n        \'type\' =&gt; \'select\',\r\n        \'renderType\' =&gt; \'selectMultipleSideBySide\',\r\n        \'foreign_table\' =&gt; \'tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd\',\r\n        \'foreign_table_where\' =&gt; \'AND {#tx_tccdexamples_domain_model_tccd}.{#sys_language_uid} = ###REC_FIELD_sys_language_uid### ORDER BY title\'\r\n\r\n    ],\r\n],</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>Other possible markers in TCA are:</p>\r\n<p>###REC_FIELD_[<em>field name</em>]###</p>\r\n<p>Any field of the current record.</p>\r\n<p>###THIS_UID###</p>\r\n<p>Current element uid (zero if new).</p>\r\n<p>###CURRENT_PID###</p>\r\n<p>The current page id (pid of the record).</p>\r\n<p>###SITEROOT###</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-tsconfig/main/en-us/PageTsconfig/TceForm.html#page_tsconfig_id\">###PAGE_TSCONFIG_ID###</a></p>\r\n<p>A value you can set from Page TSconfig dynamically.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-tsconfig/main/en-us/PageTsconfig/TceForm.html#page_tsconfig_idlist\">###PAGE_TSCONFIG_IDLIST###</a></p>\r\n<p>A value you can set from Page TSconfig dynamically.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-tsconfig/main/en-us/PageTsconfig/TceForm.html#page_tsconfig_str\">###PAGE_TSCONFIG_STR###</a></p>\r\n<p>A value you can set from Page TSconfig dynamically.</p>\r\n<p>###SITE:&lt;KEY&gt;.&lt;SUBKEY&gt;###</p>\r\n<p>A value from the site configuration, for example:&nbsp;###SITE:mySetting.categoryPid###&nbsp;or&nbsp;###SITE:rootPageId###.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-tca/main/en-us/ColumnsConfig/Type/Select/Properties/ForeignTableWhere.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-tca/main/en-us/ColumnsConfig/Type/Select/Properties/ForeignTableWhere.html</a></p>\r\n\r\n', 1, 'include-multi-select-related-dataset-form-field-in-tca-c', 0, '', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (42, 11, 1710939788, 1710939027, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Commands [19]', '<h3>1. Execute existing Symfony CLI commands</h3>\r\n<h4>1-1. Composer based TYPO3 installation</h4>\r\n<pre>\r\nvendor/bin/typo3</pre>\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\nvendor/bin/typo3 cache:flush</pre>\r\n<p>1-2. Legacy&nbsp;TYPO3 installation</p>\r\n<pre>\r\ntypo3/sysext/core/bin/typo3</pre>\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n<pre>\r\ntypo3/sysext/core/bin/typo3 cache:flush</pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Create and register new Symfony CLI commands</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/CommandControllers/Tutorial.html#console-command-tutorial\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/CommandControllers/Tutorial.html#console-command-tutorial</a></p>\r\n<p>TODO: make implementation for tccd_examples</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Modify existing CLI commands</h3>\r\n<p>Copy and modify???</p>', 1, 'commands-19', 0, '<p>This skill covers the creation of command-line commands for TYPO3, based on the Symfony Console component.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>I know how to execute existing Symfony CLI commands.</li> 	<li>I can create and register new Symfony CLI commands</li> 	<li>I can find my way around existing commands and can modify them.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (43, 11, 1711014115, 1710939844, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Extension scanner [20]', '<p>Goal 1:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>In TYPO3 Backend: Admin Tools / Upgrade / Scan Extension Files</li> 	<li>From command line: Not possible by default</li> 	<li>Static code analysis</li> </ul>\r\n<p>Goal 2:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>May show wrong positives and wrong negatives</li> </ul>\r\n\r\n', 1, 'extension-scanner-20', 0, '<p>This skill covers the Extension Scanner, which extension authors and project maintainers can use to detect possible problems in their extensions while upgrading them to a newer TYPO3 version.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>I can use the extension scanner from within the TYPO3 BE and from the command line. I know what kind of problems the scanner finds, and the limitations of the scanner.</li> 	<li>I can interpret findings of the scanner and judge whether they are relevant for my project.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (44, 11, 1711112336, 1711014215, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, NULL, , 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Flash Messages [21]', '<h3>Goal 1:</h3>\r\n<p>The severity is defined by using class constants provided by&nbsp;\\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Messaging\\FlashMessage:</p>\r\n<ul> 	<li>FlashMessage::NOTICE&nbsp;for notifications</li> 	<li>FlashMessage::INFO&nbsp;for information messages</li> 	<li>FlashMessage::OK&nbsp;for success messages</li> 	<li>FlashMessage::WARNING&nbsp;for warnings</li> 	<li>FlashMessage::ERROR&nbsp;for errors</li> </ul>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/FlashMessages/Index.html\">https://docs.typo3.org/m/typo3/reference-coreapi/11.5/en-us/ApiOverview/FlashMessages/Index.html</a></p>\r\n<h3>Goal 2:</h3>\r\n<p>JavaScript-based flash messages for TYPO3 Backend only</p>\r\n<h3>Implementation</h3>\r\n<p>File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Resources/Private/Templates/Tccd/List.html</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;f:comment&gt;Flash Messages [21]&lt;/f:comment&gt;\r\n&lt;f:flashMessages /&gt;</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Classes/Controller/TccdController.php</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Flash Messages [21] - PHP\r\n$this-&gt;addFlashMessage(\'Create new items is not possible. No user is logged in.\', \'\', \\TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Messaging\\AbstractMessage::WARNING);\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Resources/Private/Templates/Tccd/New.html</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;f:comment&gt;Flash Messages [21] - Output of FlashMessages specified in Php in Fluid Template&lt;/f:comment&gt;\r\n&lt;f:flashMessages /&gt;</pre>\r\n<p>File: typo3conf/ext/tccd_examples/Resources/Public/JavaScript/TranslationModule.js</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n// Flash Messages [21] - JavaScript\r\nrequire([\'TYPO3/CMS/Backend/Notification\'], function(Notification) {\r\n    Notification.success(\'Translation ready\', \'Datasets were translated.\');\r\n});</pre>', 1, 'flash-messages-21', 1, '<p>This skill covers flash messages, a mechanism used to communicate e.g. results of an action to the user.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<ol> 	<li>I know where the Core flash messages and notifications can be used (and where not). I know which type of flash message to use for what purpose.</li> 	<li>I can create and output flash messages using PHP, HTML and JavaScript. I can output flash messages created in existing code, e.g. other extensions.</li> </ol>', '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        (45, 0, 1711102946, 1711018135, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'TEST 900', '', 1, 'Test900', 0, NULL, '', 0, '0', 0, '', ''),
